4555/**
4556 * _scsih_send_event_to_turn_on_pfa_led - fire delayed event
4557 * @ioc: per adapter object
4558 * @handle: device handle
4559 * Context: interrupt.
4560 *
4561 * Return nothing.
4562 */
4563static void
4564_scsih_send_event_to_turn_on_pfa_led(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc, u16 handle)
4565{
4566 struct fw_event_work *fw_event;
4567
4568 fw_event = alloc_fw_event_work(0);
4569 if (!fw_event)
4570 return;
4571 fw_event->event = MPT3SAS_TURN_ON_PFA_LED;
4572 fw_event->device_handle = handle;
4573 fw_event->ioc = ioc;
4574 _scsih_fw_event_add(ioc, fw_event);
4575 fw_event_work_put(fw_event);
4576}
4577
4578/**
4579 * _scsih_smart_predicted_fault - process smart errors
4580 * @ioc: per adapter object
4581 * @handle: device handle
4582 * Context: interrupt.
4583 *
4584 * Return nothing.
4585 */
4586static void
4587_scsih_smart_predicted_fault(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc, u16 handle)
4588{
4589 struct scsi_target *starget;
4590 struct MPT3SAS_TARGET *sas_target_priv_data;
4591 Mpi2EventNotificationReply_t *event_reply;
4592 Mpi2EventDataSasDeviceStatusChange_t *event_data;
4593 struct _sas_device *sas_device;
4594 ssize_t sz;
4595 unsigned long flags;
4596
4597 /* only handle non-raid devices */
4598 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
4599 sas_device = __mpt3sas_get_sdev_by_handle(ioc, handle);
4600 if (!sas_device)
4601 goto out_unlock;
4602
4603 starget = sas_device->starget;
4604 sas_target_priv_data = starget->hostdata;
4605
4606 if ((sas_target_priv_data->flags & MPT_TARGET_FLAGS_RAID_COMPONENT) ||
4607 ((sas_target_priv_data->flags & MPT_TARGET_FLAGS_VOLUME)))
4608 goto out_unlock;
4609
4610 if (sas_device->enclosure_handle != 0)
4611 starget_printk(KERN_INFO, starget, "predicted fault, "
4612 "enclosure logical id(0x%016llx), slot(%d)\n",
4613 (unsigned long long)sas_device->enclosure_logical_id,
4614 sas_device->slot);
4615 if (sas_device->connector_name[0] != '\0')
4616 starget_printk(KERN_WARNING, starget, "predicted fault, "
4617 "enclosure level(0x%04x), connector name( %s)\n",
4618 sas_device->enclosure_level,
4619 sas_device->connector_name);
4620 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
4621
4622 if (ioc->pdev->subsystem_vendor == PCI_VENDOR_ID_IBM)
4623 _scsih_send_event_to_turn_on_pfa_led(ioc, handle);
4624
4625 /* insert into event log */
4626 sz = offsetof(Mpi2EventNotificationReply_t, EventData) +
4627 sizeof(Mpi2EventDataSasDeviceStatusChange_t);
4628 event_reply = kzalloc(sz, GFP_KERNEL);
4629 if (!event_reply) {
4630 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
4631 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
4632 goto out;
4633 }
4634
4635 event_reply->Function = MPI2_FUNCTION_EVENT_NOTIFICATION;
4636 event_reply->Event =
4637 cpu_to_le16(MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEVICE_STATUS_CHANGE);
4638 event_reply->MsgLength = sz/4;
4639 event_reply->EventDataLength =
4640 cpu_to_le16(sizeof(Mpi2EventDataSasDeviceStatusChange_t)/4);
4641 event_data = (Mpi2EventDataSasDeviceStatusChange_t *)
4642 event_reply->EventData;
4643 event_data->ReasonCode = MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEV_STAT_RC_SMART_DATA;
4644 event_data->ASC = 0x5D;
4645 event_data->DevHandle = cpu_to_le16(handle);
4646 event_data->SASAddress = cpu_to_le64(sas_target_priv_data->sas_address);
4647 mpt3sas_ctl_add_to_event_log(ioc, event_reply);
4648 kfree(event_reply);
4649out:
4650 if (sas_device)
4651 sas_device_put(sas_device);
4652 return;
4653
4654out_unlock:
4655 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
4656 goto out;
4657}
4658
4659/**
4660 * _scsih_io_done - scsi request callback
4661 * @ioc: per adapter object
4662 * @smid: system request message index
4663 * @msix_index: MSIX table index supplied by the OS
4664 * @reply: reply message frame(lower 32bit addr)
4665 *
4666 * Callback handler when using _scsih_qcmd.
4667 *
4668 * Return 1 meaning mf should be freed from _base_interrupt
4669 * 0 means the mf is freed from this function.
4670 */
4671static u8
4672_scsih_io_done(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc, u16 smid, u8 msix_index, u32 reply)
4673{
4674 Mpi2SCSIIORequest_t *mpi_request;
4675 Mpi2SCSIIOReply_t *mpi_reply;
4676 struct scsi_cmnd *scmd;
4677 u16 ioc_status;
4678 u32 xfer_cnt;
4679 u8 scsi_state;
4680 u8 scsi_status;
4681 u32 log_info;
4682 struct MPT3SAS_DEVICE *sas_device_priv_data;
4683 u32 response_code = 0;
4684 unsigned long flags;
4685
4686 mpi_reply = mpt3sas_base_get_reply_virt_addr(ioc, reply);
4687
4688 if (ioc->broadcast_aen_busy || ioc->pci_error_recovery ||
4689 ioc->got_task_abort_from_ioctl)
4690 scmd = _scsih_scsi_lookup_get_clear(ioc, smid);
4691 else
4692 scmd = __scsih_scsi_lookup_get_clear(ioc, smid);
4693
4694 if (scmd == NULL)
4695 return 1;
4696
4697 _scsih_set_satl_pending(scmd, false);
4698
4699 mpi_request = mpt3sas_base_get_msg_frame(ioc, smid);
4700
4701 if (mpi_reply == NULL) {
4702 scmd->result = DID_OK << 16;
4703 goto out;
4704 }
4705
4706 sas_device_priv_data = scmd->device->hostdata;
4707 if (!sas_device_priv_data || !sas_device_priv_data->sas_target ||
4708 sas_device_priv_data->sas_target->deleted) {
4709 scmd->result = DID_NO_CONNECT << 16;
4710 goto out;
4711 }
4712 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply->IOCStatus);
4713
4714 /*
4715 * WARPDRIVE: If direct_io is set then it is directIO,
4716 * the failed direct I/O should be redirected to volume
4717 */
4718 if (mpt3sas_scsi_direct_io_get(ioc, smid) &&
4719 ((ioc_status & MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK)
4720 != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SCSI_TASK_TERMINATED)) {
4721 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->scsi_lookup_lock, flags);
4722 ioc->scsi_lookup[smid - 1].scmd = scmd;
4723 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->scsi_lookup_lock, flags);
4724 mpt3sas_scsi_direct_io_set(ioc, smid, 0);
4725 memcpy(mpi_request->CDB.CDB32, scmd->cmnd, scmd->cmd_len);
4726 mpi_request->DevHandle =
4727 cpu_to_le16(sas_device_priv_data->sas_target->handle);
4728 ioc->put_smid_scsi_io(ioc, smid,
4729 sas_device_priv_data->sas_target->handle);
4730 return 0;
4731 }
4732 /* turning off TLR */
4733 scsi_state = mpi_reply->SCSIState;
4734 if (scsi_state & MPI2_SCSI_STATE_RESPONSE_INFO_VALID)
4735 response_code =
4736 le32_to_cpu(mpi_reply->ResponseInfo) & 0xFF;
4737 if (!sas_device_priv_data->tlr_snoop_check) {
4738 sas_device_priv_data->tlr_snoop_check++;
4739 if (!ioc->is_warpdrive &&
4740 !scsih_is_raid(&scmd->device->sdev_gendev) &&
4741 sas_is_tlr_enabled(scmd->device) &&
4742 response_code == MPI2_SCSITASKMGMT_RSP_INVALID_FRAME) {
4743 sas_disable_tlr(scmd->device);
4744 sdev_printk(KERN_INFO, scmd->device, "TLR disabled\n");
4745 }
4746 }
4747
4748 xfer_cnt = le32_to_cpu(mpi_reply->TransferCount);
4749 scsi_set_resid(scmd, scsi_bufflen(scmd) - xfer_cnt);
4750 if (ioc_status & MPI2_IOCSTATUS_FLAG_LOG_INFO_AVAILABLE)
4751 log_info = le32_to_cpu(mpi_reply->IOCLogInfo);
4752 else
4753 log_info = 0;
4754 ioc_status &= MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
4755 scsi_status = mpi_reply->SCSIStatus;
4756
4757 if (ioc_status == MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SCSI_DATA_UNDERRUN && xfer_cnt == 0 &&
4758 (scsi_status == MPI2_SCSI_STATUS_BUSY ||
4759 scsi_status == MPI2_SCSI_STATUS_RESERVATION_CONFLICT ||
4760 scsi_status == MPI2_SCSI_STATUS_TASK_SET_FULL)) {
4761 ioc_status = MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS;
4762 }
4763
4764 if (scsi_state & MPI2_SCSI_STATE_AUTOSENSE_VALID) {
4765 struct sense_info data;
4766 const void *sense_data = mpt3sas_base_get_sense_buffer(ioc,
4767 smid);
4768 u32 sz = min_t(u32, SCSI_SENSE_BUFFERSIZE,
4769 le32_to_cpu(mpi_reply->SenseCount));
4770 memcpy(scmd->sense_buffer, sense_data, sz);
4771 _scsih_normalize_sense(scmd->sense_buffer, &data);
4772 /* failure prediction threshold exceeded */
4773 if (data.asc == 0x5D)
4774 _scsih_smart_predicted_fault(ioc,
4775 le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply->DevHandle));
4776 mpt3sas_trigger_scsi(ioc, data.skey, data.asc, data.ascq);
4777
4778 if ((ioc->logging_level & MPT_DEBUG_REPLY) &&
4779 ((scmd->sense_buffer[2] == UNIT_ATTENTION) ||
4780 (scmd->sense_buffer[2] == MEDIUM_ERROR) ||
4781 (scmd->sense_buffer[2] == HARDWARE_ERROR)))
4782 _scsih_scsi_ioc_info(ioc, scmd, mpi_reply, smid);
4783 }
4784 switch (ioc_status) {
4785 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_BUSY:
4786 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES:
4787 scmd->result = SAM_STAT_BUSY;
4788 break;
4789
4790 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SCSI_DEVICE_NOT_THERE:
4791 scmd->result = DID_NO_CONNECT << 16;
4792 break;
4793
4794 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SCSI_IOC_TERMINATED:
4795 if (sas_device_priv_data->block) {
4796 scmd->result = DID_TRANSPORT_DISRUPTED << 16;
4797 goto out;
4798 }
4799 if (log_info == 0x31110630) {
4800 if (scmd->retries > 2) {
4801 scmd->result = DID_NO_CONNECT << 16;
4802 scsi_device_set_state(scmd->device,
4803 SDEV_OFFLINE);
4804 } else {
4805 scmd->result = DID_SOFT_ERROR << 16;
4806 scmd->device->expecting_cc_ua = 1;
4807 }
4808 break;
4809 } else if (log_info == VIRTUAL_IO_FAILED_RETRY) {
4810 scmd->result = DID_RESET << 16;
4811 break;
4812 } else if ((scmd->device->channel == RAID_CHANNEL) &&
4813 (scsi_state == (MPI2_SCSI_STATE_TERMINATED |
4814 MPI2_SCSI_STATE_NO_SCSI_STATUS))) {
4815 scmd->result = DID_RESET << 16;
4816 break;
4817 }
4818 scmd->result = DID_SOFT_ERROR << 16;
4819 break;
4820 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SCSI_TASK_TERMINATED:
4821 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SCSI_EXT_TERMINATED:
4822 scmd->result = DID_RESET << 16;
4823 break;
4824
4825 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SCSI_RESIDUAL_MISMATCH:
4826 if ((xfer_cnt == 0) || (scmd->underflow > xfer_cnt))
4827 scmd->result = DID_SOFT_ERROR << 16;
4828 else
4829 scmd->result = (DID_OK << 16) | scsi_status;
4830 break;
4831
4832 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SCSI_DATA_UNDERRUN:
4833 scmd->result = (DID_OK << 16) | scsi_status;
4834
4835 if ((scsi_state & MPI2_SCSI_STATE_AUTOSENSE_VALID))
4836 break;
4837
4838 if (xfer_cnt < scmd->underflow) {
4839 if (scsi_status == SAM_STAT_BUSY)
4840 scmd->result = SAM_STAT_BUSY;
4841 else
4842 scmd->result = DID_SOFT_ERROR << 16;
4843 } else if (scsi_state & (MPI2_SCSI_STATE_AUTOSENSE_FAILED |
4844 MPI2_SCSI_STATE_NO_SCSI_STATUS))
4845 scmd->result = DID_SOFT_ERROR << 16;
4846 else if (scsi_state & MPI2_SCSI_STATE_TERMINATED)
4847 scmd->result = DID_RESET << 16;
4848 else if (!xfer_cnt && scmd->cmnd[0] == REPORT_LUNS) {
4849 mpi_reply->SCSIState = MPI2_SCSI_STATE_AUTOSENSE_VALID;
4850 mpi_reply->SCSIStatus = SAM_STAT_CHECK_CONDITION;
4851 scmd->result = (DRIVER_SENSE << 24) |
4852 SAM_STAT_CHECK_CONDITION;
4853 scmd->sense_buffer[0] = 0x70;
4854 scmd->sense_buffer[2] = ILLEGAL_REQUEST;
4855 scmd->sense_buffer[12] = 0x20;
4856 scmd->sense_buffer[13] = 0;
4857 }
4858 break;
4859
4860 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SCSI_DATA_OVERRUN:
4861 scsi_set_resid(scmd, 0);
4862 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SCSI_RECOVERED_ERROR:
4863 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS:
4864 scmd->result = (DID_OK << 16) | scsi_status;
4865 if (response_code ==
4866 MPI2_SCSITASKMGMT_RSP_INVALID_FRAME ||
4867 (scsi_state & (MPI2_SCSI_STATE_AUTOSENSE_FAILED |
4868 MPI2_SCSI_STATE_NO_SCSI_STATUS)))
4869 scmd->result = DID_SOFT_ERROR << 16;
4870 else if (scsi_state & MPI2_SCSI_STATE_TERMINATED)
4871 scmd->result = DID_RESET << 16;
4872 break;
4873
4874 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_EEDP_GUARD_ERROR:
4875 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_EEDP_REF_TAG_ERROR:
4876 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_EEDP_APP_TAG_ERROR:
4877 _scsih_eedp_error_handling(scmd, ioc_status);
4878 break;
4879
4880 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SCSI_PROTOCOL_ERROR:
4881 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_INVALID_FUNCTION:
4882 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_INVALID_SGL:
4883 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_INTERNAL_ERROR:
4884 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_INVALID_FIELD:
4885 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_INVALID_STATE:
4886 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SCSI_IO_DATA_ERROR:
4887 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SCSI_TASK_MGMT_FAILED:
4888 case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_INSUFFICIENT_POWER:
4889 default:
4890 scmd->result = DID_SOFT_ERROR << 16;
4891 break;
4892
4893 }
4894
4895 if (scmd->result && (ioc->logging_level & MPT_DEBUG_REPLY))
4896 _scsih_scsi_ioc_info(ioc , scmd, mpi_reply, smid);
4897
4898 out:
4899
4900 scsi_dma_unmap(scmd);
4901
4902 scmd->scsi_done(scmd);
4903 return 1;
4904}
4905
4906/**
4907 * _scsih_sas_host_refresh - refreshing sas host object contents
4908 * @ioc: per adapter object
4909 * Context: user
4910 *
4911 * During port enable, fw will send topology events for every device. Its
4912 * possible that the handles may change from the previous setting, so this
4913 * code keeping handles updating if changed.
4914 *
4915 * Return nothing.
4916 */
4917static void
4918_scsih_sas_host_refresh(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc)
4919{
4920 u16 sz;
4921 u16 ioc_status;
4922 int i;
4923 Mpi2ConfigReply_t mpi_reply;
4924 Mpi2SasIOUnitPage0_t *sas_iounit_pg0 = NULL;
4925 u16 attached_handle;
4926 u8 link_rate;
4927
4928 dtmprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
4929 "updating handles for sas_host(0x%016llx)\n",
4930 ioc->name, (unsigned long long)ioc->sas_hba.sas_address));
4931
4932 sz = offsetof(Mpi2SasIOUnitPage0_t, PhyData) + (ioc->sas_hba.num_phys
4933 * sizeof(Mpi2SasIOUnit0PhyData_t));
4934 sas_iounit_pg0 = kzalloc(sz, GFP_KERNEL);
4935 if (!sas_iounit_pg0) {
4936 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
4937 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
4938 return;
4939 }
4940
4941 if ((mpt3sas_config_get_sas_iounit_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply,
4942 sas_iounit_pg0, sz)) != 0)
4943 goto out;
4944 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) & MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
4945 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS)
4946 goto out;
4947 for (i = 0; i < ioc->sas_hba.num_phys ; i++) {
4948 link_rate = sas_iounit_pg0->PhyData[i].NegotiatedLinkRate >> 4;
4949 if (i == 0)
4950 ioc->sas_hba.handle = le16_to_cpu(sas_iounit_pg0->
4951 PhyData[0].ControllerDevHandle);
4952 ioc->sas_hba.phy[i].handle = ioc->sas_hba.handle;
4953 attached_handle = le16_to_cpu(sas_iounit_pg0->PhyData[i].
4954 AttachedDevHandle);
4955 if (attached_handle && link_rate < MPI2_SAS_NEG_LINK_RATE_1_5)
4956 link_rate = MPI2_SAS_NEG_LINK_RATE_1_5;
4957 mpt3sas_transport_update_links(ioc, ioc->sas_hba.sas_address,
4958 attached_handle, i, link_rate);
4959 }
4960 out:
4961 kfree(sas_iounit_pg0);
4962}
4963
4964/**
4965 * _scsih_sas_host_add - create sas host object
4966 * @ioc: per adapter object
4967 *
4968 * Creating host side data object, stored in ioc->sas_hba
4969 *
4970 * Return nothing.
4971 */
4972static void
4973_scsih_sas_host_add(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc)
4974{
4975 int i;
4976 Mpi2ConfigReply_t mpi_reply;
4977 Mpi2SasIOUnitPage0_t *sas_iounit_pg0 = NULL;
4978 Mpi2SasIOUnitPage1_t *sas_iounit_pg1 = NULL;
4979 Mpi2SasPhyPage0_t phy_pg0;
4980 Mpi2SasDevicePage0_t sas_device_pg0;
4981 Mpi2SasEnclosurePage0_t enclosure_pg0;
4982 u16 ioc_status;
4983 u16 sz;
4984 u8 device_missing_delay;
4985 u8 num_phys;
4986
4987 mpt3sas_config_get_number_hba_phys(ioc, &num_phys);
4988 if (!num_phys) {
4989 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
4990 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
4991 return;
4992 }
4993 ioc->sas_hba.phy = kcalloc(num_phys,
4994 sizeof(struct _sas_phy), GFP_KERNEL);
4995 if (!ioc->sas_hba.phy) {
4996 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
4997 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
4998 goto out;
4999 }
5000 ioc->sas_hba.num_phys = num_phys;
5001
5002 /* sas_iounit page 0 */
5003 sz = offsetof(Mpi2SasIOUnitPage0_t, PhyData) + (ioc->sas_hba.num_phys *
5004 sizeof(Mpi2SasIOUnit0PhyData_t));
5005 sas_iounit_pg0 = kzalloc(sz, GFP_KERNEL);
5006 if (!sas_iounit_pg0) {
5007 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5008 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5009 return;
5010 }
5011 if ((mpt3sas_config_get_sas_iounit_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply,
5012 sas_iounit_pg0, sz))) {
5013 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5014 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5015 goto out;
5016 }
5017 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) &
5018 MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
5019 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS) {
5020 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5021 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5022 goto out;
5023 }
5024
5025 /* sas_iounit page 1 */
5026 sz = offsetof(Mpi2SasIOUnitPage1_t, PhyData) + (ioc->sas_hba.num_phys *
5027 sizeof(Mpi2SasIOUnit1PhyData_t));
5028 sas_iounit_pg1 = kzalloc(sz, GFP_KERNEL);
5029 if (!sas_iounit_pg1) {
5030 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5031 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5032 goto out;
5033 }
5034 if ((mpt3sas_config_get_sas_iounit_pg1(ioc, &mpi_reply,
5035 sas_iounit_pg1, sz))) {
5036 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5037 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5038 goto out;
5039 }
5040 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) &
5041 MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
5042 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS) {
5043 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5044 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5045 goto out;
5046 }
5047
5048 ioc->io_missing_delay =
5049 sas_iounit_pg1->IODeviceMissingDelay;
5050 device_missing_delay =
5051 sas_iounit_pg1->ReportDeviceMissingDelay;
5052 if (device_missing_delay & MPI2_SASIOUNIT1_REPORT_MISSING_UNIT_16)
5053 ioc->device_missing_delay = (device_missing_delay &
5054 MPI2_SASIOUNIT1_REPORT_MISSING_TIMEOUT_MASK) * 16;
5055 else
5056 ioc->device_missing_delay = device_missing_delay &
5057 MPI2_SASIOUNIT1_REPORT_MISSING_TIMEOUT_MASK;
5058
5059 ioc->sas_hba.parent_dev = &ioc->shost->shost_gendev;
5060 for (i = 0; i < ioc->sas_hba.num_phys ; i++) {
5061 if ((mpt3sas_config_get_phy_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply, &phy_pg0,
5062 i))) {
5063 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5064 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5065 goto out;
5066 }
5067 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) &
5068 MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
5069 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS) {
5070 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5071 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5072 goto out;
5073 }
5074
5075 if (i == 0)
5076 ioc->sas_hba.handle = le16_to_cpu(sas_iounit_pg0->
5077 PhyData[0].ControllerDevHandle);
5078 ioc->sas_hba.phy[i].handle = ioc->sas_hba.handle;
5079 ioc->sas_hba.phy[i].phy_id = i;
5080 mpt3sas_transport_add_host_phy(ioc, &ioc->sas_hba.phy[i],
5081 phy_pg0, ioc->sas_hba.parent_dev);
5082 }
5083 if ((mpt3sas_config_get_sas_device_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply, &sas_device_pg0,
5084 MPI2_SAS_DEVICE_PGAD_FORM_HANDLE, ioc->sas_hba.handle))) {
5085 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5086 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5087 goto out;
5088 }
5089 ioc->sas_hba.enclosure_handle =
5090 le16_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.EnclosureHandle);
5091 ioc->sas_hba.sas_address = le64_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.SASAddress);
5092 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
5093 "host_add: handle(0x%04x), sas_addr(0x%016llx), phys(%d)\n",
5094 ioc->name, ioc->sas_hba.handle,
5095 (unsigned long long) ioc->sas_hba.sas_address,
5096 ioc->sas_hba.num_phys) ;
5097
5098 if (ioc->sas_hba.enclosure_handle) {
5099 if (!(mpt3sas_config_get_enclosure_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply,
5100 &enclosure_pg0, MPI2_SAS_ENCLOS_PGAD_FORM_HANDLE,
5101 ioc->sas_hba.enclosure_handle)))
5102 ioc->sas_hba.enclosure_logical_id =
5103 le64_to_cpu(enclosure_pg0.EnclosureLogicalID);
5104 }
5105
5106 out:
5107 kfree(sas_iounit_pg1);
5108 kfree(sas_iounit_pg0);
5109}
5110
5111/**
5112 * _scsih_expander_add - creating expander object
5113 * @ioc: per adapter object
5114 * @handle: expander handle
5115 *
5116 * Creating expander object, stored in ioc->sas_expander_list.
5117 *
5118 * Return 0 for success, else error.
5119 */
5120static int
5121_scsih_expander_add(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc, u16 handle)
5122{
5123 struct _sas_node *sas_expander;
5124 Mpi2ConfigReply_t mpi_reply;
5125 Mpi2ExpanderPage0_t expander_pg0;
5126 Mpi2ExpanderPage1_t expander_pg1;
5127 Mpi2SasEnclosurePage0_t enclosure_pg0;
5128 u32 ioc_status;
5129 u16 parent_handle;
5130 u64 sas_address, sas_address_parent = 0;
5131 int i;
5132 unsigned long flags;
5133 struct _sas_port *mpt3sas_port = NULL;
5134
5135 int rc = 0;
5136
5137 if (!handle)
5138 return -1;
5139
5140 if (ioc->shost_recovery || ioc->pci_error_recovery)
5141 return -1;
5142
5143 if ((mpt3sas_config_get_expander_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply, &expander_pg0,
5144 MPI2_SAS_EXPAND_PGAD_FORM_HNDL, handle))) {
5145 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5146 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5147 return -1;
5148 }
5149
5150 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) &
5151 MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
5152 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS) {
5153 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5154 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5155 return -1;
5156 }
5157
5158 /* handle out of order topology events */
5159 parent_handle = le16_to_cpu(expander_pg0.ParentDevHandle);
5160 if (_scsih_get_sas_address(ioc, parent_handle, &sas_address_parent)
5161 != 0) {
5162 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5163 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5164 return -1;
5165 }
5166 if (sas_address_parent != ioc->sas_hba.sas_address) {
5167 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->sas_node_lock, flags);
5168 sas_expander = mpt3sas_scsih_expander_find_by_sas_address(ioc,
5169 sas_address_parent);
5170 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_node_lock, flags);
5171 if (!sas_expander) {
5172 rc = _scsih_expander_add(ioc, parent_handle);
5173 if (rc != 0)
5174 return rc;
5175 }
5176 }
5177
5178 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->sas_node_lock, flags);
5179 sas_address = le64_to_cpu(expander_pg0.SASAddress);
5180 sas_expander = mpt3sas_scsih_expander_find_by_sas_address(ioc,
5181 sas_address);
5182 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_node_lock, flags);
5183
5184 if (sas_expander)
5185 return 0;
5186
5187 sas_expander = kzalloc(sizeof(struct _sas_node),
5188 GFP_KERNEL);
5189 if (!sas_expander) {
5190 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5191 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5192 return -1;
5193 }
5194
5195 sas_expander->handle = handle;
5196 sas_expander->num_phys = expander_pg0.NumPhys;
5197 sas_expander->sas_address_parent = sas_address_parent;
5198 sas_expander->sas_address = sas_address;
5199
5200 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "expander_add: handle(0x%04x)," \
5201 " parent(0x%04x), sas_addr(0x%016llx), phys(%d)\n", ioc->name,
5202 handle, parent_handle, (unsigned long long)
5203 sas_expander->sas_address, sas_expander->num_phys);
5204
5205 if (!sas_expander->num_phys)
5206 goto out_fail;
5207 sas_expander->phy = kcalloc(sas_expander->num_phys,
5208 sizeof(struct _sas_phy), GFP_KERNEL);
5209 if (!sas_expander->phy) {
5210 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5211 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5212 rc = -1;
5213 goto out_fail;
5214 }
5215
5216 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&sas_expander->sas_port_list);
5217 mpt3sas_port = mpt3sas_transport_port_add(ioc, handle,
5218 sas_address_parent);
5219 if (!mpt3sas_port) {
5220 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5221 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5222 rc = -1;
5223 goto out_fail;
5224 }
5225 sas_expander->parent_dev = &mpt3sas_port->rphy->dev;
5226
5227 for (i = 0 ; i < sas_expander->num_phys ; i++) {
5228 if ((mpt3sas_config_get_expander_pg1(ioc, &mpi_reply,
5229 &expander_pg1, i, handle))) {
5230 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5231 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5232 rc = -1;
5233 goto out_fail;
5234 }
5235 sas_expander->phy[i].handle = handle;
5236 sas_expander->phy[i].phy_id = i;
5237
5238 if ((mpt3sas_transport_add_expander_phy(ioc,
5239 &sas_expander->phy[i], expander_pg1,
5240 sas_expander->parent_dev))) {
5241 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5242 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5243 rc = -1;
5244 goto out_fail;
5245 }
5246 }
5247
5248 if (sas_expander->enclosure_handle) {
5249 if (!(mpt3sas_config_get_enclosure_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply,
5250 &enclosure_pg0, MPI2_SAS_ENCLOS_PGAD_FORM_HANDLE,
5251 sas_expander->enclosure_handle)))
5252 sas_expander->enclosure_logical_id =
5253 le64_to_cpu(enclosure_pg0.EnclosureLogicalID);
5254 }
5255
5256 _scsih_expander_node_add(ioc, sas_expander);
5257 return 0;
5258
5259 out_fail:
5260
5261 if (mpt3sas_port)
5262 mpt3sas_transport_port_remove(ioc, sas_expander->sas_address,
5263 sas_address_parent);
5264 kfree(sas_expander);
5265 return rc;
5266}
5267
5268/**
5269 * mpt3sas_expander_remove - removing expander object
5270 * @ioc: per adapter object
5271 * @sas_address: expander sas_address
5272 *
5273 * Return nothing.
5274 */
5275void
5276mpt3sas_expander_remove(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc, u64 sas_address)
5277{
5278 struct _sas_node *sas_expander;
5279 unsigned long flags;
5280
5281 if (ioc->shost_recovery)
5282 return;
5283
5284 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->sas_node_lock, flags);
5285 sas_expander = mpt3sas_scsih_expander_find_by_sas_address(ioc,
5286 sas_address);
5287 if (sas_expander)
5288 list_del(&sas_expander->list);
5289 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_node_lock, flags);
5290 if (sas_expander)
5291 _scsih_expander_node_remove(ioc, sas_expander);
5292}
5293
5294/**
5295 * _scsih_done - internal SCSI_IO callback handler.
5296 * @ioc: per adapter object
5297 * @smid: system request message index
5298 * @msix_index: MSIX table index supplied by the OS
5299 * @reply: reply message frame(lower 32bit addr)
5300 *
5301 * Callback handler when sending internal generated SCSI_IO.
5302 * The callback index passed is `ioc->scsih_cb_idx`
5303 *
5304 * Return 1 meaning mf should be freed from _base_interrupt
5305 * 0 means the mf is freed from this function.
5306 */
5307static u8
5308_scsih_done(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc, u16 smid, u8 msix_index, u32 reply)
5309{
5310 MPI2DefaultReply_t *mpi_reply;
5311
5312 mpi_reply = mpt3sas_base_get_reply_virt_addr(ioc, reply);
5313 if (ioc->scsih_cmds.status == MPT3_CMD_NOT_USED)
5314 return 1;
5315 if (ioc->scsih_cmds.smid != smid)
5316 return 1;
5317 ioc->scsih_cmds.status |= MPT3_CMD_COMPLETE;
5318 if (mpi_reply) {
5319 memcpy(ioc->scsih_cmds.reply, mpi_reply,
5320 mpi_reply->MsgLength*4);
5321 ioc->scsih_cmds.status |= MPT3_CMD_REPLY_VALID;
5322 }
5323 ioc->scsih_cmds.status &= ~MPT3_CMD_PENDING;
5324 complete(&ioc->scsih_cmds.done);
5325 return 1;
5326}
5327

5329
5330
5331#define MPT3_MAX_LUNS (255)
5332
5333
5334/**
5335 * _scsih_check_access_status - check access flags
5336 * @ioc: per adapter object
5337 * @sas_address: sas address
5338 * @handle: sas device handle
5339 * @access_flags: errors returned during discovery of the device
5340 *
5341 * Return 0 for success, else failure
5342 */
5343static u8
5344_scsih_check_access_status(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc, u64 sas_address,
5345 u16 handle, u8 access_status)
5346{
5347 u8 rc = 1;
5348 char *desc = NULL;
5349
5350 switch (access_status) {
5351 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_NO_ERRORS:
5352 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_SATA_NEEDS_INITIALIZATION:
5353 rc = 0;
5354 break;
5355 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_SATA_CAPABILITY_FAILED:
5356 desc = "sata capability failed";
5357 break;
5358 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_SATA_AFFILIATION_CONFLICT:
5359 desc = "sata affiliation conflict";
5360 break;
5361 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_ROUTE_NOT_ADDRESSABLE:
5362 desc = "route not addressable";
5363 break;
5364 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_SMP_ERROR_NOT_ADDRESSABLE:
5365 desc = "smp error not addressable";
5366 break;
5367 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_DEVICE_BLOCKED:
5368 desc = "device blocked";
5369 break;
5370 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_SATA_INIT_FAILED:
5371 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_SIF_UNKNOWN:
5372 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_SIF_AFFILIATION_CONFLICT:
5373 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_SIF_DIAG:
5374 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_SIF_IDENTIFICATION:
5375 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_SIF_CHECK_POWER:
5376 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_SIF_PIO_SN:
5377 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_SIF_MDMA_SN:
5378 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_SIF_UDMA_SN:
5379 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_SIF_ZONING_VIOLATION:
5380 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_SIF_NOT_ADDRESSABLE:
5381 case MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_ASTATUS_SIF_MAX:
5382 desc = "sata initialization failed";
5383 break;
5384 default:
5385 desc = "unknown";
5386 break;
5387 }
5388
5389 if (!rc)
5390 return 0;
5391
5392 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT
5393 "discovery errors(%s): sas_address(0x%016llx), handle(0x%04x)\n",
5394 ioc->name, desc, (unsigned long long)sas_address, handle);
5395 return rc;
5396}
5397
5398/**
5399 * _scsih_check_device - checking device responsiveness
5400 * @ioc: per adapter object
5401 * @parent_sas_address: sas address of parent expander or sas host
5402 * @handle: attached device handle
5403 * @phy_numberv: phy number
5404 * @link_rate: new link rate
5405 *
5406 * Returns nothing.
5407 */
5408static void
5409_scsih_check_device(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
5410 u64 parent_sas_address, u16 handle, u8 phy_number, u8 link_rate)
5411{
5412 Mpi2ConfigReply_t mpi_reply;
5413 Mpi2SasDevicePage0_t sas_device_pg0;
5414 struct _sas_device *sas_device;
5415 u32 ioc_status;
5416 unsigned long flags;
5417 u64 sas_address;
5418 struct scsi_target *starget;
5419 struct MPT3SAS_TARGET *sas_target_priv_data;
5420 u32 device_info;
5421
5422
5423 if ((mpt3sas_config_get_sas_device_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply, &sas_device_pg0,
5424 MPI2_SAS_DEVICE_PGAD_FORM_HANDLE, handle)))
5425 return;
5426
5427 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) & MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
5428 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS)
5429 return;
5430
5431 /* wide port handling ~ we need only handle device once for the phy that
5432 * is matched in sas device page zero
5433 */
5434 if (phy_number != sas_device_pg0.PhyNum)
5435 return;
5436
5437 /* check if this is end device */
5438 device_info = le32_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.DeviceInfo);
5439 if (!(_scsih_is_end_device(device_info)))
5440 return;
5441
5442 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
5443 sas_address = le64_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.SASAddress);
5444 sas_device = __mpt3sas_get_sdev_by_addr(ioc,
5445 sas_address);
5446
5447 if (!sas_device)
5448 goto out_unlock;
5449
5450 if (unlikely(sas_device->handle != handle)) {
5451 starget = sas_device->starget;
5452 sas_target_priv_data = starget->hostdata;
5453 starget_printk(KERN_INFO, starget,
5454 "handle changed from(0x%04x) to (0x%04x)!!!\n",
5455 sas_device->handle, handle);
5456 sas_target_priv_data->handle = handle;
5457 sas_device->handle = handle;
5458 if (le16_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.Flags) &
5459 MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_FLAGS_ENCL_LEVEL_VALID) {
5460 sas_device->enclosure_level =
5461 sas_device_pg0.EnclosureLevel;
5462 memcpy(sas_device->connector_name,
5463 sas_device_pg0.ConnectorName, 4);
5464 sas_device->connector_name[4] = '\0';
5465 } else {
5466 sas_device->enclosure_level = 0;
5467 sas_device->connector_name[0] = '\0';
5468 }
5469 }
5470
5471 /* check if device is present */
5472 if (!(le16_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.Flags) &
5473 MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_FLAGS_DEVICE_PRESENT)) {
5474 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT
5475 "device is not present handle(0x%04x), flags!!!\n",
5476 ioc->name, handle);
5477 goto out_unlock;
5478 }
5479
5480 /* check if there were any issues with discovery */
5481 if (_scsih_check_access_status(ioc, sas_address, handle,
5482 sas_device_pg0.AccessStatus))
5483 goto out_unlock;
5484
5485 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
5486 _scsih_ublock_io_device(ioc, sas_address);
5487
5488 if (sas_device)
5489 sas_device_put(sas_device);
5490 return;
5491
5492out_unlock:
5493 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
5494 if (sas_device)
5495 sas_device_put(sas_device);
5496}
5497
5498/**
5499 * _scsih_add_device - creating sas device object
5500 * @ioc: per adapter object
5501 * @handle: sas device handle
5502 * @phy_num: phy number end device attached to
5503 * @is_pd: is this hidden raid component
5504 *
5505 * Creating end device object, stored in ioc->sas_device_list.
5506 *
5507 * Returns 0 for success, non-zero for failure.
5508 */
5509static int
5510_scsih_add_device(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc, u16 handle, u8 phy_num,
5511 u8 is_pd)
5512{
5513 Mpi2ConfigReply_t mpi_reply;
5514 Mpi2SasDevicePage0_t sas_device_pg0;
5515 Mpi2SasEnclosurePage0_t enclosure_pg0;
5516 struct _sas_device *sas_device;
5517 u32 ioc_status;
5518 u64 sas_address;
5519 u32 device_info;
5520
5521 if ((mpt3sas_config_get_sas_device_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply, &sas_device_pg0,
5522 MPI2_SAS_DEVICE_PGAD_FORM_HANDLE, handle))) {
5523 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5524 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5525 return -1;
5526 }
5527
5528 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) &
5529 MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
5530 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS) {
5531 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5532 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5533 return -1;
5534 }
5535
5536 /* check if this is end device */
5537 device_info = le32_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.DeviceInfo);
5538 if (!(_scsih_is_end_device(device_info)))
5539 return -1;
5540 set_bit(handle, ioc->pend_os_device_add);
5541 sas_address = le64_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.SASAddress);
5542
5543 /* check if device is present */
5544 if (!(le16_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.Flags) &
5545 MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_FLAGS_DEVICE_PRESENT)) {
5546 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "device is not present handle(0x04%x)!!!\n",
5547 ioc->name, handle);
5548 return -1;
5549 }
5550
5551 /* check if there were any issues with discovery */
5552 if (_scsih_check_access_status(ioc, sas_address, handle,
5553 sas_device_pg0.AccessStatus))
5554 return -1;
5555
5556 sas_device = mpt3sas_get_sdev_by_addr(ioc,
5557 sas_address);
5558 if (sas_device) {
5559 clear_bit(handle, ioc->pend_os_device_add);
5560 sas_device_put(sas_device);
5561 return -1;
5562 }
5563
5564 sas_device = kzalloc(sizeof(struct _sas_device),
5565 GFP_KERNEL);
5566 if (!sas_device) {
5567 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5568 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5569 return 0;
5570 }
5571
5572 kref_init(&sas_device->refcount);
5573 sas_device->handle = handle;
5574 if (_scsih_get_sas_address(ioc,
5575 le16_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.ParentDevHandle),
5576 &sas_device->sas_address_parent) != 0)
5577 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
5578 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
5579 sas_device->enclosure_handle =
5580 le16_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.EnclosureHandle);
5581 if (sas_device->enclosure_handle != 0)
5582 sas_device->slot =
5583 le16_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.Slot);
5584 sas_device->device_info = device_info;
5585 sas_device->sas_address = sas_address;
5586 sas_device->phy = sas_device_pg0.PhyNum;
5587 sas_device->fast_path = (le16_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.Flags) &
5588 MPI25_SAS_DEVICE0_FLAGS_FAST_PATH_CAPABLE) ? 1 : 0;
5589
5590 if (le16_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.Flags)
5591 & MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_FLAGS_ENCL_LEVEL_VALID) {
5592 sas_device->enclosure_level =
5593 sas_device_pg0.EnclosureLevel;
5594 memcpy(sas_device->connector_name,
5595 sas_device_pg0.ConnectorName, 4);
5596 sas_device->connector_name[4] = '\0';
5597 } else {
5598 sas_device->enclosure_level = 0;
5599 sas_device->connector_name[0] = '\0';
5600 }
5601 /* get enclosure_logical_id */
5602 if (sas_device->enclosure_handle && !(mpt3sas_config_get_enclosure_pg0(
5603 ioc, &mpi_reply, &enclosure_pg0, MPI2_SAS_ENCLOS_PGAD_FORM_HANDLE,
5604 sas_device->enclosure_handle)))
5605 sas_device->enclosure_logical_id =
5606 le64_to_cpu(enclosure_pg0.EnclosureLogicalID);
5607
5608 /* get device name */
5609 sas_device->device_name = le64_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.DeviceName);
5610
5611 if (ioc->wait_for_discovery_to_complete)
5612 _scsih_sas_device_init_add(ioc, sas_device);
5613 else
5614 _scsih_sas_device_add(ioc, sas_device);
5615
5616 sas_device_put(sas_device);
5617 return 0;
5618}
5619
5620/**
5621 * _scsih_remove_device - removing sas device object
5622 * @ioc: per adapter object
5623 * @sas_device_delete: the sas_device object
5624 *
5625 * Return nothing.
5626 */
5627static void
5628_scsih_remove_device(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
5629 struct _sas_device *sas_device)
5630{
5631 struct MPT3SAS_TARGET *sas_target_priv_data;
5632
5633 if ((ioc->pdev->subsystem_vendor == PCI_VENDOR_ID_IBM) &&
5634 (sas_device->pfa_led_on)) {
5635 _scsih_turn_off_pfa_led(ioc, sas_device);
5636 sas_device->pfa_led_on = 0;
5637 }
5638 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
5639 "%s: enter: handle(0x%04x), sas_addr(0x%016llx)\n",
5640 ioc->name, __func__,
5641 sas_device->handle, (unsigned long long)
5642 sas_device->sas_address));
5643 if (sas_device->enclosure_handle != 0)
5644 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
5645 "%s: enter: enclosure logical id(0x%016llx), slot(%d)\n",
5646 ioc->name, __func__,
5647 (unsigned long long)sas_device->enclosure_logical_id,
5648 sas_device->slot));
5649 if (sas_device->connector_name[0] != '\0')
5650 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
5651 "%s: enter: enclosure level(0x%04x), connector name( %s)\n",
5652 ioc->name, __func__,
5653 sas_device->enclosure_level,
5654 sas_device->connector_name));
5655
5656 if (sas_device->starget && sas_device->starget->hostdata) {
5657 sas_target_priv_data = sas_device->starget->hostdata;
5658 sas_target_priv_data->deleted = 1;
5659 _scsih_ublock_io_device(ioc, sas_device->sas_address);
5660 sas_target_priv_data->handle =
5661 MPT3SAS_INVALID_DEVICE_HANDLE;
5662 }
5663
5664 if (!ioc->hide_drives)
5665 mpt3sas_transport_port_remove(ioc,
5666 sas_device->sas_address,
5667 sas_device->sas_address_parent);
5668
5669 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
5670 "removing handle(0x%04x), sas_addr(0x%016llx)\n",
5671 ioc->name, sas_device->handle,
5672 (unsigned long long) sas_device->sas_address);
5673 if (sas_device->enclosure_handle != 0)
5674 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
5675 "removing : enclosure logical id(0x%016llx), slot(%d)\n",
5676 ioc->name,
5677 (unsigned long long)sas_device->enclosure_logical_id,
5678 sas_device->slot);
5679 if (sas_device->connector_name[0] != '\0')
5680 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
5681 "removing enclosure level(0x%04x), connector name( %s)\n",
5682 ioc->name, sas_device->enclosure_level,
5683 sas_device->connector_name);
5684
5685 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
5686 "%s: exit: handle(0x%04x), sas_addr(0x%016llx)\n",
5687 ioc->name, __func__,
5688 sas_device->handle, (unsigned long long)
5689 sas_device->sas_address));
5690 if (sas_device->enclosure_handle != 0)
5691 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
5692 "%s: exit: enclosure logical id(0x%016llx), slot(%d)\n",
5693 ioc->name, __func__,
5694 (unsigned long long)sas_device->enclosure_logical_id,
5695 sas_device->slot));
5696 if (sas_device->connector_name[0] != '\0')
5697 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
5698 "%s: exit: enclosure level(0x%04x), connector name(%s)\n",
5699 ioc->name, __func__, sas_device->enclosure_level,
5700 sas_device->connector_name));
5701}
5702
5703/**
5704 * _scsih_sas_topology_change_event_debug - debug for topology event
5705 * @ioc: per adapter object
5706 * @event_data: event data payload
5707 * Context: user.
5708 */
5709static void
5710_scsih_sas_topology_change_event_debug(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
5711 Mpi2EventDataSasTopologyChangeList_t *event_data)
5712{
5713 int i;
5714 u16 handle;
5715 u16 reason_code;
5716 u8 phy_number;
5717 char *status_str = NULL;
5718 u8 link_rate, prev_link_rate;
5719
5720 switch (event_data->ExpStatus) {
5721 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPO_ES_ADDED:
5722 status_str = "add";
5723 break;
5724 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPO_ES_NOT_RESPONDING:
5725 status_str = "remove";
5726 break;
5727 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPO_ES_RESPONDING:
5728 case 0:
5729 status_str = "responding";
5730 break;
5731 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPO_ES_DELAY_NOT_RESPONDING:
5732 status_str = "remove delay";
5733 break;
5734 default:
5735 status_str = "unknown status";
5736 break;
5737 }
5738 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "sas topology change: (%s)\n",
5739 ioc->name, status_str);
5740 pr_info("\thandle(0x%04x), enclosure_handle(0x%04x) " \
5741 "start_phy(%02d), count(%d)\n",
5742 le16_to_cpu(event_data->ExpanderDevHandle),
5743 le16_to_cpu(event_data->EnclosureHandle),
5744 event_data->StartPhyNum, event_data->NumEntries);
5745 for (i = 0; i < event_data->NumEntries; i++) {
5746 handle = le16_to_cpu(event_data->PHY[i].AttachedDevHandle);
5747 if (!handle)
5748 continue;
5749 phy_number = event_data->StartPhyNum + i;
5750 reason_code = event_data->PHY[i].PhyStatus &
5751 MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPO_RC_MASK;
5752 switch (reason_code) {
5753 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPO_RC_TARG_ADDED:
5754 status_str = "target add";
5755 break;
5756 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPO_RC_TARG_NOT_RESPONDING:
5757 status_str = "target remove";
5758 break;
5759 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPO_RC_DELAY_NOT_RESPONDING:
5760 status_str = "delay target remove";
5761 break;
5762 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPO_RC_PHY_CHANGED:
5763 status_str = "link rate change";
5764 break;
5765 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPO_RC_NO_CHANGE:
5766 status_str = "target responding";
5767 break;
5768 default:
5769 status_str = "unknown";
5770 break;
5771 }
5772 link_rate = event_data->PHY[i].LinkRate >> 4;
5773 prev_link_rate = event_data->PHY[i].LinkRate & 0xF;
5774 pr_info("\tphy(%02d), attached_handle(0x%04x): %s:" \
5775 " link rate: new(0x%02x), old(0x%02x)\n", phy_number,
5776 handle, status_str, link_rate, prev_link_rate);
5777
5778 }
5779}
5780
5781/**
5782 * _scsih_sas_topology_change_event - handle topology changes
5783 * @ioc: per adapter object
5784 * @fw_event: The fw_event_work object
5785 * Context: user.
5786 *
5787 */
5788static int
5789_scsih_sas_topology_change_event(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
5790 struct fw_event_work *fw_event)
5791{
5792 int i;
5793 u16 parent_handle, handle;
5794 u16 reason_code;
5795 u8 phy_number, max_phys;
5796 struct _sas_node *sas_expander;
5797 u64 sas_address;
5798 unsigned long flags;
5799 u8 link_rate, prev_link_rate;
5800 Mpi2EventDataSasTopologyChangeList_t *event_data =
5801 (Mpi2EventDataSasTopologyChangeList_t *)
5802 fw_event->event_data;
5803
5804 if (ioc->logging_level & MPT_DEBUG_EVENT_WORK_TASK)
5805 _scsih_sas_topology_change_event_debug(ioc, event_data);
5806
5807 if (ioc->shost_recovery || ioc->remove_host || ioc->pci_error_recovery)
5808 return 0;
5809
5810 if (!ioc->sas_hba.num_phys)
5811 _scsih_sas_host_add(ioc);
5812 else
5813 _scsih_sas_host_refresh(ioc);
5814
5815 if (fw_event->ignore) {
5816 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
5817 "ignoring expander event\n", ioc->name));
5818 return 0;
5819 }
5820
5821 parent_handle = le16_to_cpu(event_data->ExpanderDevHandle);
5822
5823 /* handle expander add */
5824 if (event_data->ExpStatus == MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPO_ES_ADDED)
5825 if (_scsih_expander_add(ioc, parent_handle) != 0)
5826 return 0;
5827
5828 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->sas_node_lock, flags);
5829 sas_expander = mpt3sas_scsih_expander_find_by_handle(ioc,
5830 parent_handle);
5831 if (sas_expander) {
5832 sas_address = sas_expander->sas_address;
5833 max_phys = sas_expander->num_phys;
5834 } else if (parent_handle < ioc->sas_hba.num_phys) {
5835 sas_address = ioc->sas_hba.sas_address;
5836 max_phys = ioc->sas_hba.num_phys;
5837 } else {
5838 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_node_lock, flags);
5839 return 0;
5840 }
5841 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_node_lock, flags);
5842
5843 /* handle siblings events */
5844 for (i = 0; i < event_data->NumEntries; i++) {
5845 if (fw_event->ignore) {
5846 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
5847 "ignoring expander event\n", ioc->name));
5848 return 0;
5849 }
5850 if (ioc->remove_host || ioc->pci_error_recovery)
5851 return 0;
5852 phy_number = event_data->StartPhyNum + i;
5853 if (phy_number >= max_phys)
5854 continue;
5855 reason_code = event_data->PHY[i].PhyStatus &
5856 MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPO_RC_MASK;
5857 if ((event_data->PHY[i].PhyStatus &
5858 MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPO_PHYSTATUS_VACANT) && (reason_code !=
5859 MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPO_RC_TARG_NOT_RESPONDING))
5860 continue;
5861 handle = le16_to_cpu(event_data->PHY[i].AttachedDevHandle);
5862 if (!handle)
5863 continue;
5864 link_rate = event_data->PHY[i].LinkRate >> 4;
5865 prev_link_rate = event_data->PHY[i].LinkRate & 0xF;
5866 switch (reason_code) {
5867 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPO_RC_PHY_CHANGED:
5868
5869 if (ioc->shost_recovery)
5870 break;
5871
5872 if (link_rate == prev_link_rate)
5873 break;
5874
5875 mpt3sas_transport_update_links(ioc, sas_address,
5876 handle, phy_number, link_rate);
5877
5878 if (link_rate < MPI2_SAS_NEG_LINK_RATE_1_5)
5879 break;
5880
5881 _scsih_check_device(ioc, sas_address, handle,
5882 phy_number, link_rate);
5883
5884 if (!test_bit(handle, ioc->pend_os_device_add))
5885 break;
5886
5887
5888 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPO_RC_TARG_ADDED:
5889
5890 if (ioc->shost_recovery)
5891 break;
5892
5893 mpt3sas_transport_update_links(ioc, sas_address,
5894 handle, phy_number, link_rate);
5895
5896 _scsih_add_device(ioc, handle, phy_number, 0);
5897
5898 break;
5899 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPO_RC_TARG_NOT_RESPONDING:
5900
5901 _scsih_device_remove_by_handle(ioc, handle);
5902 break;
5903 }
5904 }
5905
5906 /* handle expander removal */
5907 if (event_data->ExpStatus == MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPO_ES_NOT_RESPONDING &&
5908 sas_expander)
5909 mpt3sas_expander_remove(ioc, sas_address);
5910
5911 return 0;
5912}
5913
5914/**
5915 * _scsih_sas_device_status_change_event_debug - debug for device event
5916 * @event_data: event data payload
5917 * Context: user.
5918 *
5919 * Return nothing.
5920 */
5921static void
5922_scsih_sas_device_status_change_event_debug(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
5923 Mpi2EventDataSasDeviceStatusChange_t *event_data)
5924{
5925 char *reason_str = NULL;
5926
5927 switch (event_data->ReasonCode) {
5928 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEV_STAT_RC_SMART_DATA:
5929 reason_str = "smart data";
5930 break;
5931 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEV_STAT_RC_UNSUPPORTED:
5932 reason_str = "unsupported device discovered";
5933 break;
5934 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEV_STAT_RC_INTERNAL_DEVICE_RESET:
5935 reason_str = "internal device reset";
5936 break;
5937 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEV_STAT_RC_TASK_ABORT_INTERNAL:
5938 reason_str = "internal task abort";
5939 break;
5940 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEV_STAT_RC_ABORT_TASK_SET_INTERNAL:
5941 reason_str = "internal task abort set";
5942 break;
5943 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEV_STAT_RC_CLEAR_TASK_SET_INTERNAL:
5944 reason_str = "internal clear task set";
5945 break;
5946 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEV_STAT_RC_QUERY_TASK_INTERNAL:
5947 reason_str = "internal query task";
5948 break;
5949 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEV_STAT_RC_SATA_INIT_FAILURE:
5950 reason_str = "sata init failure";
5951 break;
5952 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEV_STAT_RC_CMP_INTERNAL_DEV_RESET:
5953 reason_str = "internal device reset complete";
5954 break;
5955 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEV_STAT_RC_CMP_TASK_ABORT_INTERNAL:
5956 reason_str = "internal task abort complete";
5957 break;
5958 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEV_STAT_RC_ASYNC_NOTIFICATION:
5959 reason_str = "internal async notification";
5960 break;
5961 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEV_STAT_RC_EXPANDER_REDUCED_FUNCTIONALITY:
5962 reason_str = "expander reduced functionality";
5963 break;
5964 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEV_STAT_RC_CMP_EXPANDER_REDUCED_FUNCTIONALITY:
5965 reason_str = "expander reduced functionality complete";
5966 break;
5967 default:
5968 reason_str = "unknown reason";
5969 break;
5970 }
5971 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "device status change: (%s)\n"
5972 "\thandle(0x%04x), sas address(0x%016llx), tag(%d)",
5973 ioc->name, reason_str, le16_to_cpu(event_data->DevHandle),
5974 (unsigned long long)le64_to_cpu(event_data->SASAddress),
5975 le16_to_cpu(event_data->TaskTag));
5976 if (event_data->ReasonCode == MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEV_STAT_RC_SMART_DATA)
5977 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT ", ASC(0x%x), ASCQ(0x%x)\n", ioc->name,
5978 event_data->ASC, event_data->ASCQ);
5979 pr_info("\n");
5980}
5981
5982/**
5983 * _scsih_sas_device_status_change_event - handle device status change
5984 * @ioc: per adapter object
5985 * @fw_event: The fw_event_work object
5986 * Context: user.
5987 *
5988 * Return nothing.
5989 */
5990static void
5991_scsih_sas_device_status_change_event(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
5992 struct fw_event_work *fw_event)
5993{
5994 struct MPT3SAS_TARGET *target_priv_data;
5995 struct _sas_device *sas_device;
5996 u64 sas_address;
5997 unsigned long flags;
5998 Mpi2EventDataSasDeviceStatusChange_t *event_data =
5999 (Mpi2EventDataSasDeviceStatusChange_t *)
6000 fw_event->event_data;
6001
6002 if (ioc->logging_level & MPT_DEBUG_EVENT_WORK_TASK)
6003 _scsih_sas_device_status_change_event_debug(ioc,
6004 event_data);
6005
6006 /* In MPI Revision K (0xC), the internal device reset complete was
6007 * implemented, so avoid setting tm_busy flag for older firmware.
6008 */
6009 if ((ioc->facts.HeaderVersion >> 8) < 0xC)
6010 return;
6011
6012 if (event_data->ReasonCode !=
6013 MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEV_STAT_RC_INTERNAL_DEVICE_RESET &&
6014 event_data->ReasonCode !=
6015 MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEV_STAT_RC_CMP_INTERNAL_DEV_RESET)
6016 return;
6017
6018 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
6019 sas_address = le64_to_cpu(event_data->SASAddress);
6020 sas_device = __mpt3sas_get_sdev_by_addr(ioc,
6021 sas_address);
6022
6023 if (!sas_device || !sas_device->starget)
6024 goto out;
6025
6026 target_priv_data = sas_device->starget->hostdata;
6027 if (!target_priv_data)
6028 goto out;
6029
6030 if (event_data->ReasonCode ==
6031 MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEV_STAT_RC_INTERNAL_DEVICE_RESET)
6032 target_priv_data->tm_busy = 1;
6033 else
6034 target_priv_data->tm_busy = 0;
6035
6036out:
6037 if (sas_device)
6038 sas_device_put(sas_device);
6039
6040 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
6041
6042}
6043
