6097/**
6098 * _scsih_sas_broadcast_primitive_event - handle broadcast events
6099 * @ioc: per adapter object
6100 * @fw_event: The fw_event_work object
6101 * Context: user.
6102 *
6103 * Return nothing.
6104 */
6105static void
6106_scsih_sas_broadcast_primitive_event(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
6107 struct fw_event_work *fw_event)
6108{
6109 struct scsi_cmnd *scmd;
6110 struct scsi_device *sdev;
6111 u16 smid, handle;
6112 u32 lun;
6113 struct MPT3SAS_DEVICE *sas_device_priv_data;
6114 u32 termination_count;
6115 u32 query_count;
6116 Mpi2SCSITaskManagementReply_t *mpi_reply;
6117 Mpi2EventDataSasBroadcastPrimitive_t *event_data =
6118 (Mpi2EventDataSasBroadcastPrimitive_t *)
6119 fw_event->event_data;
6120 u16 ioc_status;
6121 unsigned long flags;
6122 int r;
6123 u8 max_retries = 0;
6124 u8 task_abort_retries;
6125
6126 mutex_lock(&ioc->tm_cmds.mutex);
6127 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
6128 "%s: enter: phy number(%d), width(%d)\n",
6129 ioc->name, __func__, event_data->PhyNum,
6130 event_data->PortWidth);
6131
6132 _scsih_block_io_all_device(ioc);
6133
6134 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->scsi_lookup_lock, flags);
6135 mpi_reply = ioc->tm_cmds.reply;
6136 broadcast_aen_retry:
6137
6138 /* sanity checks for retrying this loop */
6139 if (max_retries++ == 5) {
6140 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "%s: giving up\n",
6141 ioc->name, __func__));
6142 goto out;
6143 } else if (max_retries > 1)
6144 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "%s: %d retry\n",
6145 ioc->name, __func__, max_retries - 1));
6146
6147 termination_count = 0;
6148 query_count = 0;
6149 for (smid = 1; smid <= ioc->scsiio_depth; smid++) {
6150 if (ioc->shost_recovery)
6151 goto out;
6152 scmd = _scsih_scsi_lookup_get(ioc, smid);
6153 if (!scmd)
6154 continue;
6155 sdev = scmd->device;
6156 sas_device_priv_data = sdev->hostdata;
6157 if (!sas_device_priv_data || !sas_device_priv_data->sas_target)
6158 continue;
6159 /* skip hidden raid components */
6160 if (sas_device_priv_data->sas_target->flags &
6161 MPT_TARGET_FLAGS_RAID_COMPONENT)
6162 continue;
6163 /* skip volumes */
6164 if (sas_device_priv_data->sas_target->flags &
6165 MPT_TARGET_FLAGS_VOLUME)
6166 continue;
6167
6168 handle = sas_device_priv_data->sas_target->handle;
6169 lun = sas_device_priv_data->lun;
6170 query_count++;
6171
6172 if (ioc->shost_recovery)
6173 goto out;
6174
6175 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->scsi_lookup_lock, flags);
6176 r = mpt3sas_scsih_issue_tm(ioc, handle, 0, 0, lun,
6177 MPI2_SCSITASKMGMT_TASKTYPE_QUERY_TASK, smid, 30);
6178 if (r == FAILED) {
6179 sdev_printk(KERN_WARNING, sdev,
6180 "mpt3sas_scsih_issue_tm: FAILED when sending "
6181 "QUERY_TASK: scmd(%p)\n", scmd);
6182 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->scsi_lookup_lock, flags);
6183 goto broadcast_aen_retry;
6184 }
6185 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply->IOCStatus)
6186 & MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
6187 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS) {
6188 sdev_printk(KERN_WARNING, sdev,
6189 "query task: FAILED with IOCSTATUS(0x%04x), scmd(%p)\n",
6190 ioc_status, scmd);
6191 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->scsi_lookup_lock, flags);
6192 goto broadcast_aen_retry;
6193 }
6194
6195 /* see if IO is still owned by IOC and target */
6196 if (mpi_reply->ResponseCode ==
6197 MPI2_SCSITASKMGMT_RSP_TM_SUCCEEDED ||
6198 mpi_reply->ResponseCode ==
6199 MPI2_SCSITASKMGMT_RSP_IO_QUEUED_ON_IOC) {
6200 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->scsi_lookup_lock, flags);
6201 continue;
6202 }
6203 task_abort_retries = 0;
6204 tm_retry:
6205 if (task_abort_retries++ == 60) {
6206 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
6207 "%s: ABORT_TASK: giving up\n", ioc->name,
6208 __func__));
6209 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->scsi_lookup_lock, flags);
6210 goto broadcast_aen_retry;
6211 }
6212
6213 if (ioc->shost_recovery)
6214 goto out_no_lock;
6215
6216 r = mpt3sas_scsih_issue_tm(ioc, handle, sdev->channel, sdev->id,
6217 sdev->lun, MPI2_SCSITASKMGMT_TASKTYPE_ABORT_TASK, smid,
6218 30);
6219 if (r == FAILED) {
6220 sdev_printk(KERN_WARNING, sdev,
6221 "mpt3sas_scsih_issue_tm: ABORT_TASK: FAILED : "
6222 "scmd(%p)\n", scmd);
6223 goto tm_retry;
6224 }
6225
6226 if (task_abort_retries > 1)
6227 sdev_printk(KERN_WARNING, sdev,
6228 "mpt3sas_scsih_issue_tm: ABORT_TASK: RETRIES (%d):"
6229 " scmd(%p)\n",
6230 task_abort_retries - 1, scmd);
6231
6232 termination_count += le32_to_cpu(mpi_reply->TerminationCount);
6233 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->scsi_lookup_lock, flags);
6234 }
6235
6236 if (ioc->broadcast_aen_pending) {
6237 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
6238 "%s: loop back due to pending AEN\n",
6239 ioc->name, __func__));
6240 ioc->broadcast_aen_pending = 0;
6241 goto broadcast_aen_retry;
6242 }
6243
6244 out:
6245 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->scsi_lookup_lock, flags);
6246 out_no_lock:
6247
6248 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
6249 "%s - exit, query_count = %d termination_count = %d\n",
6250 ioc->name, __func__, query_count, termination_count));
6251
6252 ioc->broadcast_aen_busy = 0;
6253 if (!ioc->shost_recovery)
6254 _scsih_ublock_io_all_device(ioc);
6255 mutex_unlock(&ioc->tm_cmds.mutex);
6256}
6257
6258/**
6259 * _scsih_sas_discovery_event - handle discovery events
6260 * @ioc: per adapter object
6261 * @fw_event: The fw_event_work object
6262 * Context: user.
6263 *
6264 * Return nothing.
6265 */
6266static void
6267_scsih_sas_discovery_event(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
6268 struct fw_event_work *fw_event)
6269{
6270 Mpi2EventDataSasDiscovery_t *event_data =
6271 (Mpi2EventDataSasDiscovery_t *) fw_event->event_data;
6272
6273 if (ioc->logging_level & MPT_DEBUG_EVENT_WORK_TASK) {
6274 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "discovery event: (%s)", ioc->name,
6275 (event_data->ReasonCode == MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DISC_RC_STARTED) ?
6276 "start" : "stop");
6277 if (event_data->DiscoveryStatus)
6278 pr_info("discovery_status(0x%08x)",
6279 le32_to_cpu(event_data->DiscoveryStatus));
6280 pr_info("\n");
6281 }
6282
6283 if (event_data->ReasonCode == MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DISC_RC_STARTED &&
6284 !ioc->sas_hba.num_phys) {
6285 if (disable_discovery > 0 && ioc->shost_recovery) {
6286 /* Wait for the reset to complete */
6287 while (ioc->shost_recovery)
6288 ssleep(1);
6289 }
6290 _scsih_sas_host_add(ioc);
6291 }
6292}
6293
6294/**
6295 * _scsih_ir_fastpath - turn on fastpath for IR physdisk
6296 * @ioc: per adapter object
6297 * @handle: device handle for physical disk
6298 * @phys_disk_num: physical disk number
6299 *
6300 * Return 0 for success, else failure.
6301 */
6302static int
6303_scsih_ir_fastpath(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc, u16 handle, u8 phys_disk_num)
6304{
6305 Mpi2RaidActionRequest_t *mpi_request;
6306 Mpi2RaidActionReply_t *mpi_reply;
6307 u16 smid;
6308 u8 issue_reset = 0;
6309 int rc = 0;
6310 u16 ioc_status;
6311 u32 log_info;
6312
6313 if (ioc->hba_mpi_version_belonged == MPI2_VERSION)
6314 return rc;
6315
6316 mutex_lock(&ioc->scsih_cmds.mutex);
6317
6318 if (ioc->scsih_cmds.status != MPT3_CMD_NOT_USED) {
6319 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "%s: scsih_cmd in use\n",
6320 ioc->name, __func__);
6321 rc = -EAGAIN;
6322 goto out;
6323 }
6324 ioc->scsih_cmds.status = MPT3_CMD_PENDING;
6325
6326 smid = mpt3sas_base_get_smid(ioc, ioc->scsih_cb_idx);
6327 if (!smid) {
6328 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "%s: failed obtaining a smid\n",
6329 ioc->name, __func__);
6330 ioc->scsih_cmds.status = MPT3_CMD_NOT_USED;
6331 rc = -EAGAIN;
6332 goto out;
6333 }
6334
6335 mpi_request = mpt3sas_base_get_msg_frame(ioc, smid);
6336 ioc->scsih_cmds.smid = smid;
6337 memset(mpi_request, 0, sizeof(Mpi2RaidActionRequest_t));
6338
6339 mpi_request->Function = MPI2_FUNCTION_RAID_ACTION;
6340 mpi_request->Action = MPI2_RAID_ACTION_PHYSDISK_HIDDEN;
6341 mpi_request->PhysDiskNum = phys_disk_num;
6342
6343 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "IR RAID_ACTION: turning fast "\
6344 "path on for handle(0x%04x), phys_disk_num (0x%02x)\n", ioc->name,
6345 handle, phys_disk_num));
6346
6347 init_completion(&ioc->scsih_cmds.done);
6348 ioc->put_smid_default(ioc, smid);
6349 wait_for_completion_timeout(&ioc->scsih_cmds.done, 10*HZ);
6350
6351 if (!(ioc->scsih_cmds.status & MPT3_CMD_COMPLETE)) {
6352 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "%s: timeout\n",
6353 ioc->name, __func__);
6354 if (!(ioc->scsih_cmds.status & MPT3_CMD_RESET))
6355 issue_reset = 1;
6356 rc = -EFAULT;
6357 goto out;
6358 }
6359
6360 if (ioc->scsih_cmds.status & MPT3_CMD_REPLY_VALID) {
6361
6362 mpi_reply = ioc->scsih_cmds.reply;
6363 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply->IOCStatus);
6364 if (ioc_status & MPI2_IOCSTATUS_FLAG_LOG_INFO_AVAILABLE)
6365 log_info = le32_to_cpu(mpi_reply->IOCLogInfo);
6366 else
6367 log_info = 0;
6368 ioc_status &= MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
6369 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS) {
6370 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
6371 "IR RAID_ACTION: failed: ioc_status(0x%04x), "
6372 "loginfo(0x%08x)!!!\n", ioc->name, ioc_status,
6373 log_info));
6374 rc = -EFAULT;
6375 } else
6376 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
6377 "IR RAID_ACTION: completed successfully\n",
6378 ioc->name));
6379 }
6380
6381 out:
6382 ioc->scsih_cmds.status = MPT3_CMD_NOT_USED;
6383 mutex_unlock(&ioc->scsih_cmds.mutex);
6384
6385 if (issue_reset)
6386 mpt3sas_base_hard_reset_handler(ioc, FORCE_BIG_HAMMER);
6387 return rc;
6388}
6389
6390/**
6391 * _scsih_reprobe_lun - reprobing lun
6392 * @sdev: scsi device struct
6393 * @no_uld_attach: sdev->no_uld_attach flag setting
6394 *
6395 **/
6396static void
6397_scsih_reprobe_lun(struct scsi_device *sdev, void *no_uld_attach)
6398{
6399 sdev->no_uld_attach = no_uld_attach ? 1 : 0;
6400 sdev_printk(KERN_INFO, sdev, "%s raid component\n",
6401 sdev->no_uld_attach ? "hiding" : "exposing");
6402 WARN_ON(scsi_device_reprobe(sdev));
6403}
6404
6405/**
6406 * _scsih_sas_volume_add - add new volume
6407 * @ioc: per adapter object
6408 * @element: IR config element data
6409 * Context: user.
6410 *
6411 * Return nothing.
6412 */
6413static void
6414_scsih_sas_volume_add(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
6415 Mpi2EventIrConfigElement_t *element)
6416{
6417 struct _raid_device *raid_device;
6418 unsigned long flags;
6419 u64 wwid;
6420 u16 handle = le16_to_cpu(element->VolDevHandle);
6421 int rc;
6422
6423 mpt3sas_config_get_volume_wwid(ioc, handle, &wwid);
6424 if (!wwid) {
6425 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT
6426 "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n", ioc->name,
6427 __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
6428 return;
6429 }
6430
6431 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->raid_device_lock, flags);
6432 raid_device = _scsih_raid_device_find_by_wwid(ioc, wwid);
6433 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->raid_device_lock, flags);
6434
6435 if (raid_device)
6436 return;
6437
6438 raid_device = kzalloc(sizeof(struct _raid_device), GFP_KERNEL);
6439 if (!raid_device) {
6440 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT
6441 "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n", ioc->name,
6442 __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
6443 return;
6444 }
6445
6446 raid_device->id = ioc->sas_id++;
6447 raid_device->channel = RAID_CHANNEL;
6448 raid_device->handle = handle;
6449 raid_device->wwid = wwid;
6450 _scsih_raid_device_add(ioc, raid_device);
6451 if (!ioc->wait_for_discovery_to_complete) {
6452 rc = scsi_add_device(ioc->shost, RAID_CHANNEL,
6453 raid_device->id, 0);
6454 if (rc)
6455 _scsih_raid_device_remove(ioc, raid_device);
6456 } else {
6457 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->raid_device_lock, flags);
6458 _scsih_determine_boot_device(ioc, raid_device, 1);
6459 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->raid_device_lock, flags);
6460 }
6461}
6462
6463/**
6464 * _scsih_sas_volume_delete - delete volume
6465 * @ioc: per adapter object
6466 * @handle: volume device handle
6467 * Context: user.
6468 *
6469 * Return nothing.
6470 */
6471static void
6472_scsih_sas_volume_delete(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc, u16 handle)
6473{
6474 struct _raid_device *raid_device;
6475 unsigned long flags;
6476 struct MPT3SAS_TARGET *sas_target_priv_data;
6477 struct scsi_target *starget = NULL;
6478
6479 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->raid_device_lock, flags);
6480 raid_device = mpt3sas_raid_device_find_by_handle(ioc, handle);
6481 if (raid_device) {
6482 if (raid_device->starget) {
6483 starget = raid_device->starget;
6484 sas_target_priv_data = starget->hostdata;
6485 sas_target_priv_data->deleted = 1;
6486 }
6487 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "removing handle(0x%04x), wwid(0x%016llx)\n",
6488 ioc->name, raid_device->handle,
6489 (unsigned long long) raid_device->wwid);
6490 list_del(&raid_device->list);
6491 kfree(raid_device);
6492 }
6493 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->raid_device_lock, flags);
6494 if (starget)
6495 scsi_remove_target(&starget->dev);
6496}
6497
6498/**
6499 * _scsih_sas_pd_expose - expose pd component to /dev/sdX
6500 * @ioc: per adapter object
6501 * @element: IR config element data
6502 * Context: user.
6503 *
6504 * Return nothing.
6505 */
6506static void
6507_scsih_sas_pd_expose(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
6508 Mpi2EventIrConfigElement_t *element)
6509{
6510 struct _sas_device *sas_device;
6511 struct scsi_target *starget = NULL;
6512 struct MPT3SAS_TARGET *sas_target_priv_data;
6513 unsigned long flags;
6514 u16 handle = le16_to_cpu(element->PhysDiskDevHandle);
6515
6516 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
6517 sas_device = __mpt3sas_get_sdev_by_handle(ioc, handle);
6518 if (sas_device) {
6519 sas_device->volume_handle = 0;
6520 sas_device->volume_wwid = 0;
6521 clear_bit(handle, ioc->pd_handles);
6522 if (sas_device->starget && sas_device->starget->hostdata) {
6523 starget = sas_device->starget;
6524 sas_target_priv_data = starget->hostdata;
6525 sas_target_priv_data->flags &=
6526 ~MPT_TARGET_FLAGS_RAID_COMPONENT;
6527 }
6528 }
6529 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
6530 if (!sas_device)
6531 return;
6532
6533 /* exposing raid component */
6534 if (starget)
6535 starget_for_each_device(starget, NULL, _scsih_reprobe_lun);
6536
6537 sas_device_put(sas_device);
6538}
6539
6540/**
6541 * _scsih_sas_pd_hide - hide pd component from /dev/sdX
6542 * @ioc: per adapter object
6543 * @element: IR config element data
6544 * Context: user.
6545 *
6546 * Return nothing.
6547 */
6548static void
6549_scsih_sas_pd_hide(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
6550 Mpi2EventIrConfigElement_t *element)
6551{
6552 struct _sas_device *sas_device;
6553 struct scsi_target *starget = NULL;
6554 struct MPT3SAS_TARGET *sas_target_priv_data;
6555 unsigned long flags;
6556 u16 handle = le16_to_cpu(element->PhysDiskDevHandle);
6557 u16 volume_handle = 0;
6558 u64 volume_wwid = 0;
6559
6560 mpt3sas_config_get_volume_handle(ioc, handle, &volume_handle);
6561 if (volume_handle)
6562 mpt3sas_config_get_volume_wwid(ioc, volume_handle,
6563 &volume_wwid);
6564
6565 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
6566 sas_device = __mpt3sas_get_sdev_by_handle(ioc, handle);
6567 if (sas_device) {
6568 set_bit(handle, ioc->pd_handles);
6569 if (sas_device->starget && sas_device->starget->hostdata) {
6570 starget = sas_device->starget;
6571 sas_target_priv_data = starget->hostdata;
6572 sas_target_priv_data->flags |=
6573 MPT_TARGET_FLAGS_RAID_COMPONENT;
6574 sas_device->volume_handle = volume_handle;
6575 sas_device->volume_wwid = volume_wwid;
6576 }
6577 }
6578 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
6579 if (!sas_device)
6580 return;
6581
6582 /* hiding raid component */
6583 _scsih_ir_fastpath(ioc, handle, element->PhysDiskNum);
6584
6585 if (starget)
6586 starget_for_each_device(starget, (void *)1, _scsih_reprobe_lun);
6587
6588 sas_device_put(sas_device);
6589}
6590
6591/**
6592 * _scsih_sas_pd_delete - delete pd component
6593 * @ioc: per adapter object
6594 * @element: IR config element data
6595 * Context: user.
6596 *
6597 * Return nothing.
6598 */
6599static void
6600_scsih_sas_pd_delete(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
6601 Mpi2EventIrConfigElement_t *element)
6602{
6603 u16 handle = le16_to_cpu(element->PhysDiskDevHandle);
6604
6605 _scsih_device_remove_by_handle(ioc, handle);
6606}
6607
6608/**
6609 * _scsih_sas_pd_add - remove pd component
6610 * @ioc: per adapter object
6611 * @element: IR config element data
6612 * Context: user.
6613 *
6614 * Return nothing.
6615 */
6616static void
6617_scsih_sas_pd_add(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
6618 Mpi2EventIrConfigElement_t *element)
6619{
6620 struct _sas_device *sas_device;
6621 u16 handle = le16_to_cpu(element->PhysDiskDevHandle);
6622 Mpi2ConfigReply_t mpi_reply;
6623 Mpi2SasDevicePage0_t sas_device_pg0;
6624 u32 ioc_status;
6625 u64 sas_address;
6626 u16 parent_handle;
6627
6628 set_bit(handle, ioc->pd_handles);
6629
6630 sas_device = mpt3sas_get_sdev_by_handle(ioc, handle);
6631 if (sas_device) {
6632 _scsih_ir_fastpath(ioc, handle, element->PhysDiskNum);
6633 sas_device_put(sas_device);
6634 return;
6635 }
6636
6637 if ((mpt3sas_config_get_sas_device_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply, &sas_device_pg0,
6638 MPI2_SAS_DEVICE_PGAD_FORM_HANDLE, handle))) {
6639 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
6640 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
6641 return;
6642 }
6643
6644 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) &
6645 MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
6646 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS) {
6647 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
6648 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
6649 return;
6650 }
6651
6652 parent_handle = le16_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.ParentDevHandle);
6653 if (!_scsih_get_sas_address(ioc, parent_handle, &sas_address))
6654 mpt3sas_transport_update_links(ioc, sas_address, handle,
6655 sas_device_pg0.PhyNum, MPI2_SAS_NEG_LINK_RATE_1_5);
6656
6657 _scsih_ir_fastpath(ioc, handle, element->PhysDiskNum);
6658 _scsih_add_device(ioc, handle, 0, 1);
6659}
6660
6661/**
6662 * _scsih_sas_ir_config_change_event_debug - debug for IR Config Change events
6663 * @ioc: per adapter object
6664 * @event_data: event data payload
6665 * Context: user.
6666 *
6667 * Return nothing.
6668 */
6669static void
6670_scsih_sas_ir_config_change_event_debug(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
6671 Mpi2EventDataIrConfigChangeList_t *event_data)
6672{
6673 Mpi2EventIrConfigElement_t *element;
6674 u8 element_type;
6675 int i;
6676 char *reason_str = NULL, *element_str = NULL;
6677
6678 element = (Mpi2EventIrConfigElement_t *)&event_data->ConfigElement[0];
6679
6680 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "raid config change: (%s), elements(%d)\n",
6681 ioc->name, (le32_to_cpu(event_data->Flags) &
6682 MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_FLAGS_FOREIGN_CONFIG) ?
6683 "foreign" : "native", event_data->NumElements);
6684 for (i = 0; i < event_data->NumElements; i++, element++) {
6685 switch (element->ReasonCode) {
6686 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_ADDED:
6687 reason_str = "add";
6688 break;
6689 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_REMOVED:
6690 reason_str = "remove";
6691 break;
6692 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_NO_CHANGE:
6693 reason_str = "no change";
6694 break;
6695 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_HIDE:
6696 reason_str = "hide";
6697 break;
6698 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_UNHIDE:
6699 reason_str = "unhide";
6700 break;
6701 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_VOLUME_CREATED:
6702 reason_str = "volume_created";
6703 break;
6704 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_VOLUME_DELETED:
6705 reason_str = "volume_deleted";
6706 break;
6707 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_PD_CREATED:
6708 reason_str = "pd_created";
6709 break;
6710 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_PD_DELETED:
6711 reason_str = "pd_deleted";
6712 break;
6713 default:
6714 reason_str = "unknown reason";
6715 break;
6716 }
6717 element_type = le16_to_cpu(element->ElementFlags) &
6718 MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_EFLAGS_ELEMENT_TYPE_MASK;
6719 switch (element_type) {
6720 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_EFLAGS_VOLUME_ELEMENT:
6721 element_str = "volume";
6722 break;
6723 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_EFLAGS_VOLPHYSDISK_ELEMENT:
6724 element_str = "phys disk";
6725 break;
6726 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_EFLAGS_HOTSPARE_ELEMENT:
6727 element_str = "hot spare";
6728 break;
6729 default:
6730 element_str = "unknown element";
6731 break;
6732 }
6733 pr_info("\t(%s:%s), vol handle(0x%04x), " \
6734 "pd handle(0x%04x), pd num(0x%02x)\n", element_str,
6735 reason_str, le16_to_cpu(element->VolDevHandle),
6736 le16_to_cpu(element->PhysDiskDevHandle),
6737 element->PhysDiskNum);
6738 }
6739}
6740
6741/**
6742 * _scsih_sas_ir_config_change_event - handle ir configuration change events
6743 * @ioc: per adapter object
6744 * @fw_event: The fw_event_work object
6745 * Context: user.
6746 *
6747 * Return nothing.
6748 */
6749static void
6750_scsih_sas_ir_config_change_event(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
6751 struct fw_event_work *fw_event)
6752{
6753 Mpi2EventIrConfigElement_t *element;
6754 int i;
6755 u8 foreign_config;
6756 Mpi2EventDataIrConfigChangeList_t *event_data =
6757 (Mpi2EventDataIrConfigChangeList_t *)
6758 fw_event->event_data;
6759
6760 if ((ioc->logging_level & MPT_DEBUG_EVENT_WORK_TASK) &&
6761 (!ioc->hide_ir_msg))
6762 _scsih_sas_ir_config_change_event_debug(ioc, event_data);
6763
6764 foreign_config = (le32_to_cpu(event_data->Flags) &
6765 MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_FLAGS_FOREIGN_CONFIG) ? 1 : 0;
6766
6767 element = (Mpi2EventIrConfigElement_t *)&event_data->ConfigElement[0];
6768 if (ioc->shost_recovery &&
6769 ioc->hba_mpi_version_belonged != MPI2_VERSION) {
6770 for (i = 0; i < event_data->NumElements; i++, element++) {
6771 if (element->ReasonCode == MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_HIDE)
6772 _scsih_ir_fastpath(ioc,
6773 le16_to_cpu(element->PhysDiskDevHandle),
6774 element->PhysDiskNum);
6775 }
6776 return;
6777 }
6778
6779 for (i = 0; i < event_data->NumElements; i++, element++) {
6780
6781 switch (element->ReasonCode) {
6782 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_VOLUME_CREATED:
6783 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_ADDED:
6784 if (!foreign_config)
6785 _scsih_sas_volume_add(ioc, element);
6786 break;
6787 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_VOLUME_DELETED:
6788 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_REMOVED:
6789 if (!foreign_config)
6790 _scsih_sas_volume_delete(ioc,
6791 le16_to_cpu(element->VolDevHandle));
6792 break;
6793 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_PD_CREATED:
6794 if (!ioc->is_warpdrive)
6795 _scsih_sas_pd_hide(ioc, element);
6796 break;
6797 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_PD_DELETED:
6798 if (!ioc->is_warpdrive)
6799 _scsih_sas_pd_expose(ioc, element);
6800 break;
6801 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_HIDE:
6802 if (!ioc->is_warpdrive)
6803 _scsih_sas_pd_add(ioc, element);
6804 break;
6805 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_UNHIDE:
6806 if (!ioc->is_warpdrive)
6807 _scsih_sas_pd_delete(ioc, element);
6808 break;
6809 }
6810 }
6811}
6812
6813/**
6814 * _scsih_sas_ir_volume_event - IR volume event
6815 * @ioc: per adapter object
6816 * @fw_event: The fw_event_work object
6817 * Context: user.
6818 *
6819 * Return nothing.
6820 */
6821static void
6822_scsih_sas_ir_volume_event(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
6823 struct fw_event_work *fw_event)
6824{
6825 u64 wwid;
6826 unsigned long flags;
6827 struct _raid_device *raid_device;
6828 u16 handle;
6829 u32 state;
6830 int rc;
6831 Mpi2EventDataIrVolume_t *event_data =
6832 (Mpi2EventDataIrVolume_t *) fw_event->event_data;
6833
6834 if (ioc->shost_recovery)
6835 return;
6836
6837 if (event_data->ReasonCode != MPI2_EVENT_IR_VOLUME_RC_STATE_CHANGED)
6838 return;
6839
6840 handle = le16_to_cpu(event_data->VolDevHandle);
6841 state = le32_to_cpu(event_data->NewValue);
6842 if (!ioc->hide_ir_msg)
6843 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
6844 "%s: handle(0x%04x), old(0x%08x), new(0x%08x)\n",
6845 ioc->name, __func__, handle,
6846 le32_to_cpu(event_data->PreviousValue), state));
6847 switch (state) {
6848 case MPI2_RAID_VOL_STATE_MISSING:
6849 case MPI2_RAID_VOL_STATE_FAILED:
6850 _scsih_sas_volume_delete(ioc, handle);
6851 break;
6852
6853 case MPI2_RAID_VOL_STATE_ONLINE:
6854 case MPI2_RAID_VOL_STATE_DEGRADED:
6855 case MPI2_RAID_VOL_STATE_OPTIMAL:
6856
6857 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->raid_device_lock, flags);
6858 raid_device = mpt3sas_raid_device_find_by_handle(ioc, handle);
6859 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->raid_device_lock, flags);
6860
6861 if (raid_device)
6862 break;
6863
6864 mpt3sas_config_get_volume_wwid(ioc, handle, &wwid);
6865 if (!wwid) {
6866 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT
6867 "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n", ioc->name,
6868 __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
6869 break;
6870 }
6871
6872 raid_device = kzalloc(sizeof(struct _raid_device), GFP_KERNEL);
6873 if (!raid_device) {
6874 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT
6875 "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n", ioc->name,
6876 __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
6877 break;
6878 }
6879
6880 raid_device->id = ioc->sas_id++;
6881 raid_device->channel = RAID_CHANNEL;
6882 raid_device->handle = handle;
6883 raid_device->wwid = wwid;
6884 _scsih_raid_device_add(ioc, raid_device);
6885 rc = scsi_add_device(ioc->shost, RAID_CHANNEL,
6886 raid_device->id, 0);
6887 if (rc)
6888 _scsih_raid_device_remove(ioc, raid_device);
6889 break;
6890
6891 case MPI2_RAID_VOL_STATE_INITIALIZING:
6892 default:
6893 break;
6894 }
6895}
6896
6897/**
6898 * _scsih_sas_ir_physical_disk_event - PD event
6899 * @ioc: per adapter object
6900 * @fw_event: The fw_event_work object
6901 * Context: user.
6902 *
6903 * Return nothing.
6904 */
6905static void
6906_scsih_sas_ir_physical_disk_event(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
6907 struct fw_event_work *fw_event)
6908{
6909 u16 handle, parent_handle;
6910 u32 state;
6911 struct _sas_device *sas_device;
6912 Mpi2ConfigReply_t mpi_reply;
6913 Mpi2SasDevicePage0_t sas_device_pg0;
6914 u32 ioc_status;
6915 Mpi2EventDataIrPhysicalDisk_t *event_data =
6916 (Mpi2EventDataIrPhysicalDisk_t *) fw_event->event_data;
6917 u64 sas_address;
6918
6919 if (ioc->shost_recovery)
6920 return;
6921
6922 if (event_data->ReasonCode != MPI2_EVENT_IR_PHYSDISK_RC_STATE_CHANGED)
6923 return;
6924
6925 handle = le16_to_cpu(event_data->PhysDiskDevHandle);
6926 state = le32_to_cpu(event_data->NewValue);
6927
6928 if (!ioc->hide_ir_msg)
6929 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
6930 "%s: handle(0x%04x), old(0x%08x), new(0x%08x)\n",
6931 ioc->name, __func__, handle,
6932 le32_to_cpu(event_data->PreviousValue), state));
6933
6934 switch (state) {
6935 case MPI2_RAID_PD_STATE_ONLINE:
6936 case MPI2_RAID_PD_STATE_DEGRADED:
6937 case MPI2_RAID_PD_STATE_REBUILDING:
6938 case MPI2_RAID_PD_STATE_OPTIMAL:
6939 case MPI2_RAID_PD_STATE_HOT_SPARE:
6940
6941 if (!ioc->is_warpdrive)
6942 set_bit(handle, ioc->pd_handles);
6943
6944 sas_device = mpt3sas_get_sdev_by_handle(ioc, handle);
6945 if (sas_device) {
6946 sas_device_put(sas_device);
6947 return;
6948 }
6949
6950 if ((mpt3sas_config_get_sas_device_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply,
6951 &sas_device_pg0, MPI2_SAS_DEVICE_PGAD_FORM_HANDLE,
6952 handle))) {
6953 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
6954 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
6955 return;
6956 }
6957
6958 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) &
6959 MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
6960 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS) {
6961 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
6962 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
6963 return;
6964 }
6965
6966 parent_handle = le16_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.ParentDevHandle);
6967 if (!_scsih_get_sas_address(ioc, parent_handle, &sas_address))
6968 mpt3sas_transport_update_links(ioc, sas_address, handle,
6969 sas_device_pg0.PhyNum, MPI2_SAS_NEG_LINK_RATE_1_5);
6970
6971 _scsih_add_device(ioc, handle, 0, 1);
6972
6973 break;
6974
6975 case MPI2_RAID_PD_STATE_OFFLINE:
6976 case MPI2_RAID_PD_STATE_NOT_CONFIGURED:
6977 case MPI2_RAID_PD_STATE_NOT_COMPATIBLE:
6978 default:
6979 break;
6980 }
6981}
6982
6983/**
6984 * _scsih_sas_ir_operation_status_event_debug - debug for IR op event
6985 * @ioc: per adapter object
6986 * @event_data: event data payload
6987 * Context: user.
6988 *
6989 * Return nothing.
6990 */
6991static void
6992_scsih_sas_ir_operation_status_event_debug(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
6993 Mpi2EventDataIrOperationStatus_t *event_data)
6994{
6995 char *reason_str = NULL;
6996
6997 switch (event_data->RAIDOperation) {
6998 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_RAIDOP_RESYNC:
6999 reason_str = "resync";
7000 break;
7001 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_RAIDOP_ONLINE_CAP_EXPANSION:
7002 reason_str = "online capacity expansion";
7003 break;
7004 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_RAIDOP_CONSISTENCY_CHECK:
7005 reason_str = "consistency check";
7006 break;
7007 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_RAIDOP_BACKGROUND_INIT:
7008 reason_str = "background init";
7009 break;
7010 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_RAIDOP_MAKE_DATA_CONSISTENT:
7011 reason_str = "make data consistent";
7012 break;
7013 }
7014
7015 if (!reason_str)
7016 return;
7017
7018 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "raid operational status: (%s)" \
7019 "\thandle(0x%04x), percent complete(%d)\n",
7020 ioc->name, reason_str,
7021 le16_to_cpu(event_data->VolDevHandle),
7022 event_data->PercentComplete);
7023}
7024
7025/**
7026 * _scsih_sas_ir_operation_status_event - handle RAID operation events
7027 * @ioc: per adapter object
7028 * @fw_event: The fw_event_work object
7029 * Context: user.
7030 *
7031 * Return nothing.
7032 */
7033static void
7034_scsih_sas_ir_operation_status_event(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
7035 struct fw_event_work *fw_event)
7036{
7037 Mpi2EventDataIrOperationStatus_t *event_data =
7038 (Mpi2EventDataIrOperationStatus_t *)
7039 fw_event->event_data;
7040 static struct _raid_device *raid_device;
7041 unsigned long flags;
7042 u16 handle;
7043
7044 if ((ioc->logging_level & MPT_DEBUG_EVENT_WORK_TASK) &&
7045 (!ioc->hide_ir_msg))
7046 _scsih_sas_ir_operation_status_event_debug(ioc,
7047 event_data);
7048
7049 /* code added for raid transport support */
7050 if (event_data->RAIDOperation == MPI2_EVENT_IR_RAIDOP_RESYNC) {
7051
7052 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->raid_device_lock, flags);
7053 handle = le16_to_cpu(event_data->VolDevHandle);
7054 raid_device = mpt3sas_raid_device_find_by_handle(ioc, handle);
7055 if (raid_device)
7056 raid_device->percent_complete =
7057 event_data->PercentComplete;
7058 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->raid_device_lock, flags);
7059 }
7060}
7061
7062/**
7063 * _scsih_prep_device_scan - initialize parameters prior to device scan
7064 * @ioc: per adapter object
7065 *
7066 * Set the deleted flag prior to device scan. If the device is found during
7067 * the scan, then we clear the deleted flag.
7068 */
7069static void
7070_scsih_prep_device_scan(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc)
7071{
7072 struct MPT3SAS_DEVICE *sas_device_priv_data;
7073 struct scsi_device *sdev;
7074
7075 shost_for_each_device(sdev, ioc->shost) {
7076 sas_device_priv_data = sdev->hostdata;
7077 if (sas_device_priv_data && sas_device_priv_data->sas_target)
7078 sas_device_priv_data->sas_target->deleted = 1;
7079 }
7080}
7081
7082/**
7083 * _scsih_mark_responding_sas_device - mark a sas_devices as responding
7084 * @ioc: per adapter object
7085 * @sas_device_pg0: SAS Device page 0
7086 *
7087 * After host reset, find out whether devices are still responding.
7088 * Used in _scsih_remove_unresponsive_sas_devices.
7089 *
7090 * Return nothing.
7091 */
7092static void
7093_scsih_mark_responding_sas_device(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
7094Mpi2SasDevicePage0_t *sas_device_pg0)
7095{
7096 struct MPT3SAS_TARGET *sas_target_priv_data = NULL;
7097 struct scsi_target *starget;
7098 struct _sas_device *sas_device;
7099 unsigned long flags;
7100
7101 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
7102 list_for_each_entry(sas_device, &ioc->sas_device_list, list) {
7103 if ((sas_device->sas_address == sas_device_pg0->SASAddress) &&
7104 (sas_device->slot == sas_device_pg0->Slot)) {
7105 sas_device->responding = 1;
7106 starget = sas_device->starget;
7107 if (starget && starget->hostdata) {
7108 sas_target_priv_data = starget->hostdata;
7109 sas_target_priv_data->tm_busy = 0;
7110 sas_target_priv_data->deleted = 0;
7111 } else
7112 sas_target_priv_data = NULL;
7113 if (starget) {
7114 starget_printk(KERN_INFO, starget,
7115 "handle(0x%04x), sas_addr(0x%016llx)\n",
7116 sas_device_pg0->DevHandle,
7117 (unsigned long long)
7118 sas_device->sas_address);
7119
7120 if (sas_device->enclosure_handle != 0)
7121 starget_printk(KERN_INFO, starget,
7122 "enclosure logical id(0x%016llx),"
7123 " slot(%d)\n",
7124 (unsigned long long)
7125 sas_device->enclosure_logical_id,
7126 sas_device->slot);
7127 }
7128 if (sas_device_pg0->Flags &
7129 MPI2_SAS_DEVICE0_FLAGS_ENCL_LEVEL_VALID) {
7130 sas_device->enclosure_level =
7131 sas_device_pg0->EnclosureLevel;
7132 memcpy(&sas_device->connector_name[0],
7133 &sas_device_pg0->ConnectorName[0], 4);
7134 } else {
7135 sas_device->enclosure_level = 0;
7136 sas_device->connector_name[0] = '\0';
7137 }
7138
7139 if (sas_device->handle == sas_device_pg0->DevHandle)
7140 goto out;
7141 pr_info("\thandle changed from(0x%04x)!!!\n",
7142 sas_device->handle);
7143 sas_device->handle = sas_device_pg0->DevHandle;
7144 if (sas_target_priv_data)
7145 sas_target_priv_data->handle =
7146 sas_device_pg0->DevHandle;
7147 goto out;
7148 }
7149 }
7150 out:
7151 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
7152}
7153
7154/**
7155 * _scsih_search_responding_sas_devices -
7156 * @ioc: per adapter object
7157 *
7158 * After host reset, find out whether devices are still responding.
7159 * If not remove.
7160 *
7161 * Return nothing.
7162 */
7163static void
7164_scsih_search_responding_sas_devices(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc)
7165{
7166 Mpi2SasDevicePage0_t sas_device_pg0;
7167 Mpi2ConfigReply_t mpi_reply;
7168 u16 ioc_status;
7169 u16 handle;
7170 u32 device_info;
7171
7172 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "search for end-devices: start\n", ioc->name);
7173
7174 if (list_empty(&ioc->sas_device_list))
7175 goto out;
7176
7177 handle = 0xFFFF;
7178 while (!(mpt3sas_config_get_sas_device_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply,
7179 &sas_device_pg0, MPI2_SAS_DEVICE_PGAD_FORM_GET_NEXT_HANDLE,
7180 handle))) {
7181 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) &
7182 MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
7183 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS)
7184 break;
7185 handle = sas_device_pg0.DevHandle =
7186 le16_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.DevHandle);
7187 device_info = le32_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.DeviceInfo);
7188 if (!(_scsih_is_end_device(device_info)))
7189 continue;
7190 sas_device_pg0.SASAddress =
7191 le64_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.SASAddress);
7192 sas_device_pg0.Slot = le16_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.Slot);
7193 sas_device_pg0.Flags = le16_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.Flags);
7194 _scsih_mark_responding_sas_device(ioc, &sas_device_pg0);
7195 }
7196
7197 out:
7198 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "search for end-devices: complete\n",
7199 ioc->name);
7200}
7201
7202/**
7203 * _scsih_mark_responding_raid_device - mark a raid_device as responding
7204 * @ioc: per adapter object
7205 * @wwid: world wide identifier for raid volume
7206 * @handle: device handle
7207 *
7208 * After host reset, find out whether devices are still responding.
7209 * Used in _scsih_remove_unresponsive_raid_devices.
7210 *
7211 * Return nothing.
7212 */
7213static void
7214_scsih_mark_responding_raid_device(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc, u64 wwid,
7215 u16 handle)
7216{
7217 struct MPT3SAS_TARGET *sas_target_priv_data = NULL;
7218 struct scsi_target *starget;
7219 struct _raid_device *raid_device;
7220 unsigned long flags;
7221
7222 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->raid_device_lock, flags);
7223 list_for_each_entry(raid_device, &ioc->raid_device_list, list) {
7224 if (raid_device->wwid == wwid && raid_device->starget) {
7225 starget = raid_device->starget;
7226 if (starget && starget->hostdata) {
7227 sas_target_priv_data = starget->hostdata;
7228 sas_target_priv_data->deleted = 0;
7229 } else
7230 sas_target_priv_data = NULL;
7231 raid_device->responding = 1;
7232 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->raid_device_lock, flags);
7233 starget_printk(KERN_INFO, raid_device->starget,
7234 "handle(0x%04x), wwid(0x%016llx)\n", handle,
7235 (unsigned long long)raid_device->wwid);
7236
7237 /*
7238 * WARPDRIVE: The handles of the PDs might have changed
7239 * across the host reset so re-initialize the
7240 * required data for Direct IO
7241 */
7242 mpt3sas_init_warpdrive_properties(ioc, raid_device);
7243 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->raid_device_lock, flags);
7244 if (raid_device->handle == handle) {
7245 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->raid_device_lock,
7246 flags);
7247 return;
7248 }
7249 pr_info("\thandle changed from(0x%04x)!!!\n",
7250 raid_device->handle);
7251 raid_device->handle = handle;
7252 if (sas_target_priv_data)
7253 sas_target_priv_data->handle = handle;
7254 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->raid_device_lock, flags);
7255 return;
7256 }
7257 }
7258 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->raid_device_lock, flags);
7259}
7260
7261/**
7262 * _scsih_search_responding_raid_devices -
7263 * @ioc: per adapter object
7264 *
7265 * After host reset, find out whether devices are still responding.
7266 * If not remove.
7267 *
7268 * Return nothing.
7269 */
7270static void
7271_scsih_search_responding_raid_devices(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc)
7272{
7273 Mpi2RaidVolPage1_t volume_pg1;
7274 Mpi2RaidVolPage0_t volume_pg0;
7275 Mpi2RaidPhysDiskPage0_t pd_pg0;
7276 Mpi2ConfigReply_t mpi_reply;
7277 u16 ioc_status;
7278 u16 handle;
7279 u8 phys_disk_num;
7280
7281 if (!ioc->ir_firmware)
7282 return;
7283
7284 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "search for raid volumes: start\n",
7285 ioc->name);
7286
7287 if (list_empty(&ioc->raid_device_list))
7288 goto out;
7289
7290 handle = 0xFFFF;
7291 while (!(mpt3sas_config_get_raid_volume_pg1(ioc, &mpi_reply,
7292 &volume_pg1, MPI2_RAID_VOLUME_PGAD_FORM_GET_NEXT_HANDLE, handle))) {
7293 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) &
7294 MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
7295 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS)
7296 break;
7297 handle = le16_to_cpu(volume_pg1.DevHandle);
7298
7299 if (mpt3sas_config_get_raid_volume_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply,
7300 &volume_pg0, MPI2_RAID_VOLUME_PGAD_FORM_HANDLE, handle,
7301 sizeof(Mpi2RaidVolPage0_t)))
7302 continue;
7303
7304 if (volume_pg0.VolumeState == MPI2_RAID_VOL_STATE_OPTIMAL ||
7305 volume_pg0.VolumeState == MPI2_RAID_VOL_STATE_ONLINE ||
7306 volume_pg0.VolumeState == MPI2_RAID_VOL_STATE_DEGRADED)
7307 _scsih_mark_responding_raid_device(ioc,
7308 le64_to_cpu(volume_pg1.WWID), handle);
7309 }
7310
7311 /* refresh the pd_handles */
7312 if (!ioc->is_warpdrive) {
7313 phys_disk_num = 0xFF;
7314 memset(ioc->pd_handles, 0, ioc->pd_handles_sz);
7315 while (!(mpt3sas_config_get_phys_disk_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply,
7316 &pd_pg0, MPI2_PHYSDISK_PGAD_FORM_GET_NEXT_PHYSDISKNUM,
7317 phys_disk_num))) {
7318 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) &
7319 MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
7320 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS)
7321 break;
7322 phys_disk_num = pd_pg0.PhysDiskNum;
7323 handle = le16_to_cpu(pd_pg0.DevHandle);
7324 set_bit(handle, ioc->pd_handles);
7325 }
7326 }
7327 out:
7328 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "search for responding raid volumes: complete\n",
7329 ioc->name);
7330}
7331
7332/**
7333 * _scsih_mark_responding_expander - mark a expander as responding
7334 * @ioc: per adapter object
7335 * @sas_address: sas address
7336 * @handle:
7337 *
7338 * After host reset, find out whether devices are still responding.
7339 * Used in _scsih_remove_unresponsive_expanders.
7340 *
7341 * Return nothing.
7342 */
7343static void
7344_scsih_mark_responding_expander(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc, u64 sas_address,
7345 u16 handle)
7346{
7347 struct _sas_node *sas_expander;
7348 unsigned long flags;
7349 int i;
7350
7351 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->sas_node_lock, flags);
7352 list_for_each_entry(sas_expander, &ioc->sas_expander_list, list) {
7353 if (sas_expander->sas_address != sas_address)
7354 continue;
7355 sas_expander->responding = 1;
7356 if (sas_expander->handle == handle)
7357 goto out;
7358 pr_info("\texpander(0x%016llx): handle changed" \
7359 " from(0x%04x) to (0x%04x)!!!\n",
7360 (unsigned long long)sas_expander->sas_address,
7361 sas_expander->handle, handle);
7362 sas_expander->handle = handle;
7363 for (i = 0 ; i < sas_expander->num_phys ; i++)
7364 sas_expander->phy[i].handle = handle;
7365 goto out;
7366 }
7367 out:
7368 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_node_lock, flags);
7369}
7370
7371/**
7372 * _scsih_search_responding_expanders -
7373 * @ioc: per adapter object
7374 *
7375 * After host reset, find out whether devices are still responding.
7376 * If not remove.
7377 *
7378 * Return nothing.
7379 */
7380static void
7381_scsih_search_responding_expanders(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc)
7382{
7383 Mpi2ExpanderPage0_t expander_pg0;
7384 Mpi2ConfigReply_t mpi_reply;
7385 u16 ioc_status;
7386 u64 sas_address;
7387 u16 handle;
7388
7389 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "search for expanders: start\n", ioc->name);
7390
7391 if (list_empty(&ioc->sas_expander_list))
7392 goto out;
7393
7394 handle = 0xFFFF;
7395 while (!(mpt3sas_config_get_expander_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply, &expander_pg0,
7396 MPI2_SAS_EXPAND_PGAD_FORM_GET_NEXT_HNDL, handle))) {
7397
7398 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) &
7399 MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
7400 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS)
7401 break;
7402
7403 handle = le16_to_cpu(expander_pg0.DevHandle);
7404 sas_address = le64_to_cpu(expander_pg0.SASAddress);
7405 pr_info("\texpander present: handle(0x%04x), sas_addr(0x%016llx)\n",
7406 handle,
7407 (unsigned long long)sas_address);
7408 _scsih_mark_responding_expander(ioc, sas_address, handle);
7409 }
7410
7411 out:
7412 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "search for expanders: complete\n", ioc->name);
7413}
7414
7415/**
7416 * _scsih_remove_unresponding_sas_devices - removing unresponding devices
7417 * @ioc: per adapter object
7418 *
7419 * Return nothing.
7420 */
7421static void
7422_scsih_remove_unresponding_sas_devices(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc)
7423{
7424 struct _sas_device *sas_device, *sas_device_next;
7425 struct _sas_node *sas_expander, *sas_expander_next;
7426 struct _raid_device *raid_device, *raid_device_next;
7427 struct list_head tmp_list;
7428 unsigned long flags;
7429 LIST_HEAD(head);
7430
7431 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "removing unresponding devices: start\n",
7432 ioc->name);
7433
7434 /* removing unresponding end devices */
7435 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "removing unresponding devices: end-devices\n",
7436 ioc->name);
7437 /*
7438 * Iterate, pulling off devices marked as non-responding. We become the
7439 * owner for the reference the list had on any object we prune.
7440 */
7441 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
7442 list_for_each_entry_safe(sas_device, sas_device_next,
7443 &ioc->sas_device_list, list) {
7444 if (!sas_device->responding)
7445 list_move_tail(&sas_device->list, &head);
7446 else
7447 sas_device->responding = 0;
7448 }
7449 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
7450
7451 /*
7452 * Now, uninitialize and remove the unresponding devices we pruned.
7453 */
7454 list_for_each_entry_safe(sas_device, sas_device_next, &head, list) {
7455 _scsih_remove_device(ioc, sas_device);
7456 list_del_init(&sas_device->list);
7457 sas_device_put(sas_device);
7458 }
7459
7460 /* removing unresponding volumes */
7461 if (ioc->ir_firmware) {
7462 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "removing unresponding devices: volumes\n",
7463 ioc->name);
7464 list_for_each_entry_safe(raid_device, raid_device_next,
7465 &ioc->raid_device_list, list) {
7466 if (!raid_device->responding)
7467 _scsih_sas_volume_delete(ioc,
7468 raid_device->handle);
7469 else
7470 raid_device->responding = 0;
7471 }
7472 }
7473
7474 /* removing unresponding expanders */
7475 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "removing unresponding devices: expanders\n",
7476 ioc->name);
7477 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->sas_node_lock, flags);
7478 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&tmp_list);
7479 list_for_each_entry_safe(sas_expander, sas_expander_next,
7480 &ioc->sas_expander_list, list) {
7481 if (!sas_expander->responding)
7482 list_move_tail(&sas_expander->list, &tmp_list);
7483 else
7484 sas_expander->responding = 0;
7485 }
7486 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_node_lock, flags);
7487 list_for_each_entry_safe(sas_expander, sas_expander_next, &tmp_list,
7488 list) {
7489 list_del(&sas_expander->list);
7490 _scsih_expander_node_remove(ioc, sas_expander);
7491 }
7492
7493 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "removing unresponding devices: complete\n",
7494 ioc->name);
7495
7496 /* unblock devices */
7497 _scsih_ublock_io_all_device(ioc);
7498}
7499
7500static void
7501_scsih_refresh_expander_links(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
7502 struct _sas_node *sas_expander, u16 handle)
7503{
7504 Mpi2ExpanderPage1_t expander_pg1;
7505 Mpi2ConfigReply_t mpi_reply;
7506 int i;
7507
7508 for (i = 0 ; i < sas_expander->num_phys ; i++) {
7509 if ((mpt3sas_config_get_expander_pg1(ioc, &mpi_reply,
7510 &expander_pg1, i, handle))) {
7511 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
7512 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
7513 return;
7514 }
7515
7516 mpt3sas_transport_update_links(ioc, sas_expander->sas_address,
7517 le16_to_cpu(expander_pg1.AttachedDevHandle), i,
7518 expander_pg1.NegotiatedLinkRate >> 4);
7519 }
7520}
7521
7522/**
7523 * _scsih_scan_for_devices_after_reset - scan for devices after host reset
7524 * @ioc: per adapter object
7525 *
7526 * Return nothing.
7527 */
7528static void
7529_scsih_scan_for_devices_after_reset(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc)
7530{
7531 Mpi2ExpanderPage0_t expander_pg0;
7532 Mpi2SasDevicePage0_t sas_device_pg0;
7533 Mpi2RaidVolPage1_t volume_pg1;
7534 Mpi2RaidVolPage0_t volume_pg0;
7535 Mpi2RaidPhysDiskPage0_t pd_pg0;
7536 Mpi2EventIrConfigElement_t element;
7537 Mpi2ConfigReply_t mpi_reply;
7538 u8 phys_disk_num;
7539 u16 ioc_status;
7540 u16 handle, parent_handle;
7541 u64 sas_address;
7542 struct _sas_device *sas_device;
7543 struct _sas_node *expander_device;
7544 static struct _raid_device *raid_device;
7545 u8 retry_count;
7546 unsigned long flags;
7547
7548 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "scan devices: start\n", ioc->name);
7549
7550 _scsih_sas_host_refresh(ioc);
7551
7552 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tscan devices: expanders start\n", ioc->name);
7553
7554 /* expanders */
7555 handle = 0xFFFF;
7556 while (!(mpt3sas_config_get_expander_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply, &expander_pg0,
7557 MPI2_SAS_EXPAND_PGAD_FORM_GET_NEXT_HNDL, handle))) {
7558 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) &
7559 MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
7560 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS) {
7561 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tbreak from expander scan: " \
7562 "ioc_status(0x%04x), loginfo(0x%08x)\n",
7563 ioc->name, ioc_status,
7564 le32_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCLogInfo));
7565 break;
7566 }
7567 handle = le16_to_cpu(expander_pg0.DevHandle);
7568 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->sas_node_lock, flags);
7569 expander_device = mpt3sas_scsih_expander_find_by_sas_address(
7570 ioc, le64_to_cpu(expander_pg0.SASAddress));
7571 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_node_lock, flags);
7572 if (expander_device)
7573 _scsih_refresh_expander_links(ioc, expander_device,
7574 handle);
7575 else {
7576 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tBEFORE adding expander: " \
7577 "handle (0x%04x), sas_addr(0x%016llx)\n", ioc->name,
7578 handle, (unsigned long long)
7579 le64_to_cpu(expander_pg0.SASAddress));
7580 _scsih_expander_add(ioc, handle);
7581 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tAFTER adding expander: " \
7582 "handle (0x%04x), sas_addr(0x%016llx)\n", ioc->name,
7583 handle, (unsigned long long)
7584 le64_to_cpu(expander_pg0.SASAddress));
7585 }
7586 }
7587
7588 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tscan devices: expanders complete\n",
7589 ioc->name);
7590
7591 if (!ioc->ir_firmware)
7592 goto skip_to_sas;
7593
7594 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tscan devices: phys disk start\n", ioc->name);
7595
7596 /* phys disk */
7597 phys_disk_num = 0xFF;
7598 while (!(mpt3sas_config_get_phys_disk_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply,
7599 &pd_pg0, MPI2_PHYSDISK_PGAD_FORM_GET_NEXT_PHYSDISKNUM,
7600 phys_disk_num))) {
7601 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) &
7602 MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
7603 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS) {
7604 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tbreak from phys disk scan: "\
7605 "ioc_status(0x%04x), loginfo(0x%08x)\n",
7606 ioc->name, ioc_status,
7607 le32_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCLogInfo));
7608 break;
7609 }
7610 phys_disk_num = pd_pg0.PhysDiskNum;
7611 handle = le16_to_cpu(pd_pg0.DevHandle);
7612 sas_device = mpt3sas_get_sdev_by_handle(ioc, handle);
7613 if (sas_device) {
7614 sas_device_put(sas_device);
7615 continue;
7616 }
7617 if (mpt3sas_config_get_sas_device_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply,
7618 &sas_device_pg0, MPI2_SAS_DEVICE_PGAD_FORM_HANDLE,
7619 handle) != 0)
7620 continue;
7621 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) &
7622 MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
7623 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS) {
7624 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tbreak from phys disk scan " \
7625 "ioc_status(0x%04x), loginfo(0x%08x)\n",
7626 ioc->name, ioc_status,
7627 le32_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCLogInfo));
7628 break;
7629 }
7630 parent_handle = le16_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.ParentDevHandle);
7631 if (!_scsih_get_sas_address(ioc, parent_handle,
7632 &sas_address)) {
7633 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tBEFORE adding phys disk: " \
7634 " handle (0x%04x), sas_addr(0x%016llx)\n",
7635 ioc->name, handle, (unsigned long long)
7636 le64_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.SASAddress));
7637 mpt3sas_transport_update_links(ioc, sas_address,
7638 handle, sas_device_pg0.PhyNum,
7639 MPI2_SAS_NEG_LINK_RATE_1_5);
7640 set_bit(handle, ioc->pd_handles);
7641 retry_count = 0;
7642 /* This will retry adding the end device.
7643 * _scsih_add_device() will decide on retries and
7644 * return "1" when it should be retried
7645 */
7646 while (_scsih_add_device(ioc, handle, retry_count++,
7647 1)) {
7648 ssleep(1);
7649 }
7650 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tAFTER adding phys disk: " \
7651 " handle (0x%04x), sas_addr(0x%016llx)\n",
7652 ioc->name, handle, (unsigned long long)
7653 le64_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.SASAddress));
7654 }
7655 }
7656
7657 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tscan devices: phys disk complete\n",
7658 ioc->name);
7659
7660 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tscan devices: volumes start\n", ioc->name);
7661
7662 /* volumes */
7663 handle = 0xFFFF;
7664 while (!(mpt3sas_config_get_raid_volume_pg1(ioc, &mpi_reply,
7665 &volume_pg1, MPI2_RAID_VOLUME_PGAD_FORM_GET_NEXT_HANDLE, handle))) {
7666 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) &
7667 MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
7668 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS) {
7669 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tbreak from volume scan: " \
7670 "ioc_status(0x%04x), loginfo(0x%08x)\n",
7671 ioc->name, ioc_status,
7672 le32_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCLogInfo));
7673 break;
7674 }
7675 handle = le16_to_cpu(volume_pg1.DevHandle);
7676 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->raid_device_lock, flags);
7677 raid_device = _scsih_raid_device_find_by_wwid(ioc,
7678 le64_to_cpu(volume_pg1.WWID));
7679 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->raid_device_lock, flags);
7680 if (raid_device)
7681 continue;
7682 if (mpt3sas_config_get_raid_volume_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply,
7683 &volume_pg0, MPI2_RAID_VOLUME_PGAD_FORM_HANDLE, handle,
7684 sizeof(Mpi2RaidVolPage0_t)))
7685 continue;
7686 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) &
7687 MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
7688 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS) {
7689 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tbreak from volume scan: " \
7690 "ioc_status(0x%04x), loginfo(0x%08x)\n",
7691 ioc->name, ioc_status,
7692 le32_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCLogInfo));
7693 break;
7694 }
7695 if (volume_pg0.VolumeState == MPI2_RAID_VOL_STATE_OPTIMAL ||
7696 volume_pg0.VolumeState == MPI2_RAID_VOL_STATE_ONLINE ||
7697 volume_pg0.VolumeState == MPI2_RAID_VOL_STATE_DEGRADED) {
7698 memset(&element, 0, sizeof(Mpi2EventIrConfigElement_t));
7699 element.ReasonCode = MPI2_EVENT_IR_CHANGE_RC_ADDED;
7700 element.VolDevHandle = volume_pg1.DevHandle;
7701 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
7702 "\tBEFORE adding volume: handle (0x%04x)\n",
7703 ioc->name, volume_pg1.DevHandle);
7704 _scsih_sas_volume_add(ioc, &element);
7705 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
7706 "\tAFTER adding volume: handle (0x%04x)\n",
7707 ioc->name, volume_pg1.DevHandle);
7708 }
7709 }
7710
7711 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tscan devices: volumes complete\n",
7712 ioc->name);
7713
7714 skip_to_sas:
7715
7716 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tscan devices: end devices start\n",
7717 ioc->name);
7718
7719 /* sas devices */
7720 handle = 0xFFFF;
7721 while (!(mpt3sas_config_get_sas_device_pg0(ioc, &mpi_reply,
7722 &sas_device_pg0, MPI2_SAS_DEVICE_PGAD_FORM_GET_NEXT_HANDLE,
7723 handle))) {
7724 ioc_status = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCStatus) &
7725 MPI2_IOCSTATUS_MASK;
7726 if (ioc_status != MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SUCCESS) {
7727 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tbreak from end device scan:"\
7728 " ioc_status(0x%04x), loginfo(0x%08x)\n",
7729 ioc->name, ioc_status,
7730 le32_to_cpu(mpi_reply.IOCLogInfo));
7731 break;
7732 }
7733 handle = le16_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.DevHandle);
7734 if (!(_scsih_is_end_device(
7735 le32_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.DeviceInfo))))
7736 continue;
7737 sas_device = mpt3sas_get_sdev_by_addr(ioc,
7738 le64_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.SASAddress));
7739 if (sas_device) {
7740 sas_device_put(sas_device);
7741 continue;
7742 }
7743 parent_handle = le16_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.ParentDevHandle);
7744 if (!_scsih_get_sas_address(ioc, parent_handle, &sas_address)) {
7745 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tBEFORE adding end device: " \
7746 "handle (0x%04x), sas_addr(0x%016llx)\n", ioc->name,
7747 handle, (unsigned long long)
7748 le64_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.SASAddress));
7749 mpt3sas_transport_update_links(ioc, sas_address, handle,
7750 sas_device_pg0.PhyNum, MPI2_SAS_NEG_LINK_RATE_1_5);
7751 retry_count = 0;
7752 /* This will retry adding the end device.
7753 * _scsih_add_device() will decide on retries and
7754 * return "1" when it should be retried
7755 */
7756 while (_scsih_add_device(ioc, handle, retry_count++,
7757 0)) {
7758 ssleep(1);
7759 }
7760 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tAFTER adding end device: " \
7761 "handle (0x%04x), sas_addr(0x%016llx)\n", ioc->name,
7762 handle, (unsigned long long)
7763 le64_to_cpu(sas_device_pg0.SASAddress));
7764 }
7765 }
7766 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "\tscan devices: end devices complete\n",
7767 ioc->name);
7768
7769 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "scan devices: complete\n", ioc->name);
7770}
7771/**
7772 * mpt3sas_scsih_reset_handler - reset callback handler (for scsih)
7773 * @ioc: per adapter object
7774 * @reset_phase: phase
7775 *
7776 * The handler for doing any required cleanup or initialization.
7777 *
7778 * The reset phase can be MPT3_IOC_PRE_RESET, MPT3_IOC_AFTER_RESET,
7779 * MPT3_IOC_DONE_RESET
7780 *
7781 * Return nothing.
7782 */
7783void
7784mpt3sas_scsih_reset_handler(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc, int reset_phase)
7785{
7786 switch (reset_phase) {
7787 case MPT3_IOC_PRE_RESET:
7788 dtmprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
7789 "%s: MPT3_IOC_PRE_RESET\n", ioc->name, __func__));
7790 break;
7791 case MPT3_IOC_AFTER_RESET:
7792 dtmprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
7793 "%s: MPT3_IOC_AFTER_RESET\n", ioc->name, __func__));
7794 if (ioc->scsih_cmds.status & MPT3_CMD_PENDING) {
7795 ioc->scsih_cmds.status |= MPT3_CMD_RESET;
7796 mpt3sas_base_free_smid(ioc, ioc->scsih_cmds.smid);
7797 complete(&ioc->scsih_cmds.done);
7798 }
7799 if (ioc->tm_cmds.status & MPT3_CMD_PENDING) {
7800 ioc->tm_cmds.status |= MPT3_CMD_RESET;
7801 mpt3sas_base_free_smid(ioc, ioc->tm_cmds.smid);
7802 complete(&ioc->tm_cmds.done);
7803 }
7804
7805 memset(ioc->pend_os_device_add, 0, ioc->pend_os_device_add_sz);
7806 memset(ioc->device_remove_in_progress, 0,
7807 ioc->device_remove_in_progress_sz);
7808 _scsih_fw_event_cleanup_queue(ioc);
7809 _scsih_flush_running_cmds(ioc);
7810 break;
7811 case MPT3_IOC_DONE_RESET:
7812 dtmprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
7813 "%s: MPT3_IOC_DONE_RESET\n", ioc->name, __func__));
7814 if ((!ioc->is_driver_loading) && !(disable_discovery > 0 &&
7815 !ioc->sas_hba.num_phys)) {
7816 _scsih_prep_device_scan(ioc);
7817 _scsih_search_responding_sas_devices(ioc);
7818 _scsih_search_responding_raid_devices(ioc);
7819 _scsih_search_responding_expanders(ioc);
7820 _scsih_error_recovery_delete_devices(ioc);
7821 }
7822 break;
7823 }
7824}
7825
7826/**
7827 * _mpt3sas_fw_work - delayed task for processing firmware events
7828 * @ioc: per adapter object
7829 * @fw_event: The fw_event_work object
7830 * Context: user.
7831 *
7832 * Return nothing.
7833 */
7834static void
7835_mpt3sas_fw_work(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc, struct fw_event_work *fw_event)
7836{
7837 _scsih_fw_event_del_from_list(ioc, fw_event);
7838
7839 /* the queue is being flushed so ignore this event */
7840 if (ioc->remove_host || ioc->pci_error_recovery) {
7841 fw_event_work_put(fw_event);
7842 return;
7843 }
7844
7845 switch (fw_event->event) {
7846 case MPT3SAS_PROCESS_TRIGGER_DIAG:
7847 mpt3sas_process_trigger_data(ioc,
7848 (struct SL_WH_TRIGGERS_EVENT_DATA_T *)
7849 fw_event->event_data);
7850 break;
7851 case MPT3SAS_REMOVE_UNRESPONDING_DEVICES:
7852 while (scsi_host_in_recovery(ioc->shost) ||
7853 ioc->shost_recovery) {
7854 /*
7855 * If we're unloading, bail. Otherwise, this can become
7856 * an infinite loop.
7857 */
7858 if (ioc->remove_host)
7859 goto out;
7860 ssleep(1);
7861 }
7862 _scsih_remove_unresponding_sas_devices(ioc);
7863 _scsih_scan_for_devices_after_reset(ioc);
7864 break;
7865 case MPT3SAS_PORT_ENABLE_COMPLETE:
7866 ioc->start_scan = 0;
7867 if (missing_delay[0] != -1 && missing_delay[1] != -1)
7868 mpt3sas_base_update_missing_delay(ioc, missing_delay[0],
7869 missing_delay[1]);
7870 dewtprintk(ioc, pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
7871 "port enable: complete from worker thread\n",
7872 ioc->name));
7873 break;
7874 case MPT3SAS_TURN_ON_PFA_LED:
7875 _scsih_turn_on_pfa_led(ioc, fw_event->device_handle);
7876 break;
7877 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPOLOGY_CHANGE_LIST:
7878 _scsih_sas_topology_change_event(ioc, fw_event);
7879 break;
7880 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEVICE_STATUS_CHANGE:
7881 _scsih_sas_device_status_change_event(ioc, fw_event);
7882 break;
7883 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DISCOVERY:
7884 _scsih_sas_discovery_event(ioc, fw_event);
7885 break;
7886 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_BROADCAST_PRIMITIVE:
7887 _scsih_sas_broadcast_primitive_event(ioc, fw_event);
7888 break;
7889 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_ENCL_DEVICE_STATUS_CHANGE:
7890 _scsih_sas_enclosure_dev_status_change_event(ioc,
7891 fw_event);
7892 break;
7893 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CONFIGURATION_CHANGE_LIST:
7894 _scsih_sas_ir_config_change_event(ioc, fw_event);
7895 break;
7896 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_VOLUME:
7897 _scsih_sas_ir_volume_event(ioc, fw_event);
7898 break;
7899 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_PHYSICAL_DISK:
7900 _scsih_sas_ir_physical_disk_event(ioc, fw_event);
7901 break;
7902 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_OPERATION_STATUS:
7903 _scsih_sas_ir_operation_status_event(ioc, fw_event);
7904 break;
7905 }
7906out:
7907 fw_event_work_put(fw_event);
7908}
7909
7910/**
7911 * _firmware_event_work
7912 * @ioc: per adapter object
7913 * @work: The fw_event_work object
7914 * Context: user.
7915 *
7916 * wrappers for the work thread handling firmware events
7917 *
7918 * Return nothing.
7919 */
7920
7921static void
7922_firmware_event_work(struct work_struct *work)
7923{
7924 struct fw_event_work *fw_event = container_of(work,
7925 struct fw_event_work, work);
7926
7927 _mpt3sas_fw_work(fw_event->ioc, fw_event);
7928}
7929
7930/**
7931 * mpt3sas_scsih_event_callback - firmware event handler (called at ISR time)
7932 * @ioc: per adapter object
7933 * @msix_index: MSIX table index supplied by the OS
7934 * @reply: reply message frame(lower 32bit addr)
7935 * Context: interrupt.
7936 *
7937 * This function merely adds a new work task into ioc->firmware_event_thread.
7938 * The tasks are worked from _firmware_event_work in user context.
7939 *
7940 * Return 1 meaning mf should be freed from _base_interrupt
7941 * 0 means the mf is freed from this function.
7942 */
7943u8
7944mpt3sas_scsih_event_callback(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc, u8 msix_index,
7945 u32 reply)
7946{
7947 struct fw_event_work *fw_event;
7948 Mpi2EventNotificationReply_t *mpi_reply;
7949 u16 event;
7950 u16 sz;
7951 Mpi26EventDataActiveCableExcept_t *ActiveCableEventData;
7952
7953 /* events turned off due to host reset or driver unloading */
7954 if (ioc->remove_host || ioc->pci_error_recovery)
7955 return 1;
7956
7957 mpi_reply = mpt3sas_base_get_reply_virt_addr(ioc, reply);
7958
7959 if (unlikely(!mpi_reply)) {
7960 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "mpi_reply not valid at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
7961 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
7962 return 1;
7963 }
7964
7965 event = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply->Event);
7966
7967 if (event != MPI2_EVENT_LOG_ENTRY_ADDED)
7968 mpt3sas_trigger_event(ioc, event, 0);
7969
7970 switch (event) {
7971 /* handle these */
7972 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_BROADCAST_PRIMITIVE:
7973 {
7974 Mpi2EventDataSasBroadcastPrimitive_t *baen_data =
7975 (Mpi2EventDataSasBroadcastPrimitive_t *)
7976 mpi_reply->EventData;
7977
7978 if (baen_data->Primitive !=
7979 MPI2_EVENT_PRIMITIVE_ASYNCHRONOUS_EVENT)
7980 return 1;
7981
7982 if (ioc->broadcast_aen_busy) {
7983 ioc->broadcast_aen_pending++;
7984 return 1;
7985 } else
7986 ioc->broadcast_aen_busy = 1;
7987 break;
7988 }
7989
7990 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_TOPOLOGY_CHANGE_LIST:
7991 _scsih_check_topo_delete_events(ioc,
7992 (Mpi2EventDataSasTopologyChangeList_t *)
7993 mpi_reply->EventData);
7994 break;
7995 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_CONFIGURATION_CHANGE_LIST:
7996 _scsih_check_ir_config_unhide_events(ioc,
7997 (Mpi2EventDataIrConfigChangeList_t *)
7998 mpi_reply->EventData);
7999 break;
8000 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_VOLUME:
8001 _scsih_check_volume_delete_events(ioc,
8002 (Mpi2EventDataIrVolume_t *)
8003 mpi_reply->EventData);
8004 break;
8005 case MPI2_EVENT_LOG_ENTRY_ADDED:
8006 {
8007 Mpi2EventDataLogEntryAdded_t *log_entry;
8008 u32 *log_code;
8009
8010 if (!ioc->is_warpdrive)
8011 break;
8012
8013 log_entry = (Mpi2EventDataLogEntryAdded_t *)
8014 mpi_reply->EventData;
8015 log_code = (u32 *)log_entry->LogData;
8016
8017 if (le16_to_cpu(log_entry->LogEntryQualifier)
8018 != MPT2_WARPDRIVE_LOGENTRY)
8019 break;
8020
8021 switch (le32_to_cpu(*log_code)) {
8022 case MPT2_WARPDRIVE_LC_SSDT:
8023 pr_warn(MPT3SAS_FMT "WarpDrive Warning: "
8024 "IO Throttling has occurred in the WarpDrive "
8025 "subsystem. Check WarpDrive documentation for "
8026 "additional details.\n", ioc->name);
8027 break;
8028 case MPT2_WARPDRIVE_LC_SSDLW:
8029 pr_warn(MPT3SAS_FMT "WarpDrive Warning: "
8030 "Program/Erase Cycles for the WarpDrive subsystem "
8031 "in degraded range. Check WarpDrive documentation "
8032 "for additional details.\n", ioc->name);
8033 break;
8034 case MPT2_WARPDRIVE_LC_SSDLF:
8035 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "WarpDrive Fatal Error: "
8036 "There are no Program/Erase Cycles for the "
8037 "WarpDrive subsystem. The storage device will be "
8038 "in read-only mode. Check WarpDrive documentation "
8039 "for additional details.\n", ioc->name);
8040 break;
8041 case MPT2_WARPDRIVE_LC_BRMF:
8042 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "WarpDrive Fatal Error: "
8043 "The Backup Rail Monitor has failed on the "
8044 "WarpDrive subsystem. Check WarpDrive "
8045 "documentation for additional details.\n",
8046 ioc->name);
8047 break;
8048 }
8049
8050 break;
8051 }
8052 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DEVICE_STATUS_CHANGE:
8053 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_OPERATION_STATUS:
8054 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_DISCOVERY:
8055 case MPI2_EVENT_SAS_ENCL_DEVICE_STATUS_CHANGE:
8056 case MPI2_EVENT_IR_PHYSICAL_DISK:
8057 break;
8058
8059 case MPI2_EVENT_TEMP_THRESHOLD:
8060 _scsih_temp_threshold_events(ioc,
8061 (Mpi2EventDataTemperature_t *)
8062 mpi_reply->EventData);
8063 break;
8064 case MPI2_EVENT_ACTIVE_CABLE_EXCEPTION:
8065 ActiveCableEventData =
8066 (Mpi26EventDataActiveCableExcept_t *) mpi_reply->EventData;
8067 switch (ActiveCableEventData->ReasonCode) {
8068 case MPI26_EVENT_ACTIVE_CABLE_INSUFFICIENT_POWER:
8069 pr_notice(MPT3SAS_FMT "Receptacle ID %d: This active cable"
8070 " requires %d mW of power\n", ioc->name,
8071 ActiveCableEventData->ReceptacleID,
8072 ActiveCableEventData->ActiveCablePowerRequirement);
8073 pr_notice(MPT3SAS_FMT "Receptacle ID %d: Devices connected"
8074 " to this active cable will not be seen\n",
8075 ioc->name, ActiveCableEventData->ReceptacleID);
8076 break;
8077
8078 case MPI26_EVENT_ACTIVE_CABLE_DEGRADED:
8079 pr_notice(MPT3SAS_FMT "ReceptacleID %d: This cable",
8080 ioc->name, ActiveCableEventData->ReceptacleID);
8081 pr_notice(" is not running at an optimal speed(12 Gb/s)\n");
8082 break;
8083 }
8084
8085 break;
8086
8087 default: /* ignore the rest */
8088 return 1;
8089 }
8090
8091 sz = le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply->EventDataLength) * 4;
8092 fw_event = alloc_fw_event_work(sz);
8093 if (!fw_event) {
8094 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
8095 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
8096 return 1;
8097 }
8098
8099 memcpy(fw_event->event_data, mpi_reply->EventData, sz);
8100 fw_event->ioc = ioc;
8101 fw_event->VF_ID = mpi_reply->VF_ID;
8102 fw_event->VP_ID = mpi_reply->VP_ID;
8103 fw_event->event = event;
8104 _scsih_fw_event_add(ioc, fw_event);
8105 fw_event_work_put(fw_event);
8106 return 1;
8107}
8108
8109/**
8110 * _scsih_expander_node_remove - removing expander device from list.
8111 * @ioc: per adapter object
8112 * @sas_expander: the sas_device object
8113 * Context: Calling function should acquire ioc->sas_node_lock.
8114 *
8115 * Removing object and freeing associated memory from the
8116 * ioc->sas_expander_list.
8117 *
8118 * Return nothing.
8119 */
8120static void
8121_scsih_expander_node_remove(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
8122 struct _sas_node *sas_expander)
8123{
8124 struct _sas_port *mpt3sas_port, *next;
8125
8126 /* remove sibling ports attached to this expander */
8127 list_for_each_entry_safe(mpt3sas_port, next,
8128 &sas_expander->sas_port_list, port_list) {
8129 if (ioc->shost_recovery)
8130 return;
8131 if (mpt3sas_port->remote_identify.device_type ==
8132 SAS_END_DEVICE)
8133 mpt3sas_device_remove_by_sas_address(ioc,
8134 mpt3sas_port->remote_identify.sas_address);
8135 else if (mpt3sas_port->remote_identify.device_type ==
8136 SAS_EDGE_EXPANDER_DEVICE ||
8137 mpt3sas_port->remote_identify.device_type ==
8138 SAS_FANOUT_EXPANDER_DEVICE)
8139 mpt3sas_expander_remove(ioc,
8140 mpt3sas_port->remote_identify.sas_address);
8141 }
8142
8143 mpt3sas_transport_port_remove(ioc, sas_expander->sas_address,
8144 sas_expander->sas_address_parent);
8145
8146 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
8147 "expander_remove: handle(0x%04x), sas_addr(0x%016llx)\n",
8148 ioc->name,
8149 sas_expander->handle, (unsigned long long)
8150 sas_expander->sas_address);
8151
8152 kfree(sas_expander->phy);
8153 kfree(sas_expander);
8154}
8155
8156/**
8157 * _scsih_ir_shutdown - IR shutdown notification
8158 * @ioc: per adapter object
8159 *
8160 * Sending RAID Action to alert the Integrated RAID subsystem of the IOC that
8161 * the host system is shutting down.
8162 *
8163 * Return nothing.
8164 */
8165static void
8166_scsih_ir_shutdown(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc)
8167{
8168 Mpi2RaidActionRequest_t *mpi_request;
8169 Mpi2RaidActionReply_t *mpi_reply;
8170 u16 smid;
8171
8172 /* is IR firmware build loaded ? */
8173 if (!ioc->ir_firmware)
8174 return;
8175
8176 /* are there any volumes ? */
8177 if (list_empty(&ioc->raid_device_list))
8178 return;
8179
8180 mutex_lock(&ioc->scsih_cmds.mutex);
8181
8182 if (ioc->scsih_cmds.status != MPT3_CMD_NOT_USED) {
8183 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "%s: scsih_cmd in use\n",
8184 ioc->name, __func__);
8185 goto out;
8186 }
8187 ioc->scsih_cmds.status = MPT3_CMD_PENDING;
8188
8189 smid = mpt3sas_base_get_smid(ioc, ioc->scsih_cb_idx);
8190 if (!smid) {
8191 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "%s: failed obtaining a smid\n",
8192 ioc->name, __func__);
8193 ioc->scsih_cmds.status = MPT3_CMD_NOT_USED;
8194 goto out;
8195 }
8196
8197 mpi_request = mpt3sas_base_get_msg_frame(ioc, smid);
8198 ioc->scsih_cmds.smid = smid;
8199 memset(mpi_request, 0, sizeof(Mpi2RaidActionRequest_t));
8200
8201 mpi_request->Function = MPI2_FUNCTION_RAID_ACTION;
8202 mpi_request->Action = MPI2_RAID_ACTION_SYSTEM_SHUTDOWN_INITIATED;
8203
8204 if (!ioc->hide_ir_msg)
8205 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "IR shutdown (sending)\n", ioc->name);
8206 init_completion(&ioc->scsih_cmds.done);
8207 ioc->put_smid_default(ioc, smid);
8208 wait_for_completion_timeout(&ioc->scsih_cmds.done, 10*HZ);
8209
8210 if (!(ioc->scsih_cmds.status & MPT3_CMD_COMPLETE)) {
8211 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "%s: timeout\n",
8212 ioc->name, __func__);
8213 goto out;
8214 }
8215
8216 if (ioc->scsih_cmds.status & MPT3_CMD_REPLY_VALID) {
8217 mpi_reply = ioc->scsih_cmds.reply;
8218 if (!ioc->hide_ir_msg)
8219 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "IR shutdown "
8220 "(complete): ioc_status(0x%04x), loginfo(0x%08x)\n",
8221 ioc->name, le16_to_cpu(mpi_reply->IOCStatus),
8222 le32_to_cpu(mpi_reply->IOCLogInfo));
8223 }
8224
8225 out:
8226 ioc->scsih_cmds.status = MPT3_CMD_NOT_USED;
8227 mutex_unlock(&ioc->scsih_cmds.mutex);
8228}
8229
8230/**
8231 * scsih_remove - detach and remove add host
8232 * @pdev: PCI device struct
8233 *
8234 * Routine called when unloading the driver.
8235 * Return nothing.
8236 */
8237static void scsih_remove(struct pci_dev *pdev)
8238{
8239 struct Scsi_Host *shost = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
8240 struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc = shost_priv(shost);
8241 struct _sas_port *mpt3sas_port, *next_port;
8242 struct _raid_device *raid_device, *next;
8243 struct MPT3SAS_TARGET *sas_target_priv_data;
8244 struct workqueue_struct *wq;
8245 unsigned long flags;
8246
8247 ioc->remove_host = 1;
8248
8249 mpt3sas_wait_for_commands_to_complete(ioc);
8250 _scsih_flush_running_cmds(ioc);
8251
8252 _scsih_fw_event_cleanup_queue(ioc);
8253
8254 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->fw_event_lock, flags);
8255 wq = ioc->firmware_event_thread;
8256 ioc->firmware_event_thread = NULL;
8257 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->fw_event_lock, flags);
8258 if (wq)
8259 destroy_workqueue(wq);
8260
8261 /* release all the volumes */
8262 _scsih_ir_shutdown(ioc);
8263 list_for_each_entry_safe(raid_device, next, &ioc->raid_device_list,
8264 list) {
8265 if (raid_device->starget) {
8266 sas_target_priv_data =
8267 raid_device->starget->hostdata;
8268 sas_target_priv_data->deleted = 1;
8269 scsi_remove_target(&raid_device->starget->dev);
8270 }
8271 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "removing handle(0x%04x), wwid(0x%016llx)\n",
8272 ioc->name, raid_device->handle,
8273 (unsigned long long) raid_device->wwid);
8274 _scsih_raid_device_remove(ioc, raid_device);
8275 }
8276
8277 /* free ports attached to the sas_host */
8278 list_for_each_entry_safe(mpt3sas_port, next_port,
8279 &ioc->sas_hba.sas_port_list, port_list) {
8280 if (mpt3sas_port->remote_identify.device_type ==
8281 SAS_END_DEVICE)
8282 mpt3sas_device_remove_by_sas_address(ioc,
8283 mpt3sas_port->remote_identify.sas_address);
8284 else if (mpt3sas_port->remote_identify.device_type ==
8285 SAS_EDGE_EXPANDER_DEVICE ||
8286 mpt3sas_port->remote_identify.device_type ==
8287 SAS_FANOUT_EXPANDER_DEVICE)
8288 mpt3sas_expander_remove(ioc,
8289 mpt3sas_port->remote_identify.sas_address);
8290 }
8291
8292 /* free phys attached to the sas_host */
8293 if (ioc->sas_hba.num_phys) {
8294 kfree(ioc->sas_hba.phy);
8295 ioc->sas_hba.phy = NULL;
8296 ioc->sas_hba.num_phys = 0;
8297 }
8298
8299 sas_remove_host(shost);
8300 mpt3sas_base_detach(ioc);
8301 spin_lock(&gioc_lock);
8302 list_del(&ioc->list);
8303 spin_unlock(&gioc_lock);
8304 scsi_host_put(shost);
8305}
8306
8307/**
8308 * scsih_shutdown - routine call during system shutdown
8309 * @pdev: PCI device struct
8310 *
8311 * Return nothing.
8312 */
8313static void
8314scsih_shutdown(struct pci_dev *pdev)
8315{
8316 struct Scsi_Host *shost = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
8317 struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc = shost_priv(shost);
8318 struct workqueue_struct *wq;
8319 unsigned long flags;
8320
8321 ioc->remove_host = 1;
8322
8323 mpt3sas_wait_for_commands_to_complete(ioc);
8324 _scsih_flush_running_cmds(ioc);
8325
8326 _scsih_fw_event_cleanup_queue(ioc);
8327
8328 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->fw_event_lock, flags);
8329 wq = ioc->firmware_event_thread;
8330 ioc->firmware_event_thread = NULL;
8331 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->fw_event_lock, flags);
8332 if (wq)
8333 destroy_workqueue(wq);
8334
8335 _scsih_ir_shutdown(ioc);
8336 mpt3sas_base_detach(ioc);
8337}
8338
8339
8340/**
8341 * _scsih_probe_boot_devices - reports 1st device
8342 * @ioc: per adapter object
8343 *
8344 * If specified in bios page 2, this routine reports the 1st
8345 * device scsi-ml or sas transport for persistent boot device
8346 * purposes. Please refer to function _scsih_determine_boot_device()
8347 */
8348static void
8349_scsih_probe_boot_devices(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc)
8350{
8351 u8 is_raid;
8352 void *device;
8353 struct _sas_device *sas_device;
8354 struct _raid_device *raid_device;
8355 u16 handle;
8356 u64 sas_address_parent;
8357 u64 sas_address;
8358 unsigned long flags;
8359 int rc;
8360
8361 /* no Bios, return immediately */
8362 if (!ioc->bios_pg3.BiosVersion)
8363 return;
8364
8365 device = NULL;
8366 is_raid = 0;
8367 if (ioc->req_boot_device.device) {
8368 device = ioc->req_boot_device.device;
8369 is_raid = ioc->req_boot_device.is_raid;
8370 } else if (ioc->req_alt_boot_device.device) {
8371 device = ioc->req_alt_boot_device.device;
8372 is_raid = ioc->req_alt_boot_device.is_raid;
8373 } else if (ioc->current_boot_device.device) {
8374 device = ioc->current_boot_device.device;
8375 is_raid = ioc->current_boot_device.is_raid;
8376 }
8377
8378 if (!device)
8379 return;
8380
8381 if (is_raid) {
8382 raid_device = device;
8383 rc = scsi_add_device(ioc->shost, RAID_CHANNEL,
8384 raid_device->id, 0);
8385 if (rc)
8386 _scsih_raid_device_remove(ioc, raid_device);
8387 } else {
8388 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
8389 sas_device = device;
8390 handle = sas_device->handle;
8391 sas_address_parent = sas_device->sas_address_parent;
8392 sas_address = sas_device->sas_address;
8393 list_move_tail(&sas_device->list, &ioc->sas_device_list);
8394 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
8395
8396 if (ioc->hide_drives)
8397 return;
8398 if (!mpt3sas_transport_port_add(ioc, handle,
8399 sas_address_parent)) {
8400 _scsih_sas_device_remove(ioc, sas_device);
8401 } else if (!sas_device->starget) {
8402 if (!ioc->is_driver_loading) {
8403 mpt3sas_transport_port_remove(ioc,
8404 sas_address,
8405 sas_address_parent);
8406 _scsih_sas_device_remove(ioc, sas_device);
8407 }
8408 }
8409 }
8410}
8411
8412/**
8413 * _scsih_probe_raid - reporting raid volumes to scsi-ml
8414 * @ioc: per adapter object
8415 *
8416 * Called during initial loading of the driver.
8417 */
8418static void
8419_scsih_probe_raid(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc)
8420{
8421 struct _raid_device *raid_device, *raid_next;
8422 int rc;
8423
8424 list_for_each_entry_safe(raid_device, raid_next,
8425 &ioc->raid_device_list, list) {
8426 if (raid_device->starget)
8427 continue;
8428 rc = scsi_add_device(ioc->shost, RAID_CHANNEL,
8429 raid_device->id, 0);
8430 if (rc)
8431 _scsih_raid_device_remove(ioc, raid_device);
8432 }
8433}
8434
8435static struct _sas_device *get_next_sas_device(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc)
8436{
8437 struct _sas_device *sas_device = NULL;
8438 unsigned long flags;
8439
8440 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
8441 if (!list_empty(&ioc->sas_device_init_list)) {
8442 sas_device = list_first_entry(&ioc->sas_device_init_list,
8443 struct _sas_device, list);
8444 sas_device_get(sas_device);
8445 }
8446 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
8447
8448 return sas_device;
8449}
8450
8451static void sas_device_make_active(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc,
8452 struct _sas_device *sas_device)
8453{
8454 unsigned long flags;
8455
8456 spin_lock_irqsave(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
8457
8458 /*
8459 * Since we dropped the lock during the call to port_add(), we need to
8460 * be careful here that somebody else didn't move or delete this item
8461 * while we were busy with other things.
8462 *
8463 * If it was on the list, we need a put() for the reference the list
8464 * had. Either way, we need a get() for the destination list.
8465 */
8466 if (!list_empty(&sas_device->list)) {
8467 list_del_init(&sas_device->list);
8468 sas_device_put(sas_device);
8469 }
8470
8471 sas_device_get(sas_device);
8472 list_add_tail(&sas_device->list, &ioc->sas_device_list);
8473
8474 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&ioc->sas_device_lock, flags);
8475}
8476
8477/**
8478 * _scsih_probe_sas - reporting sas devices to sas transport
8479 * @ioc: per adapter object
8480 *
8481 * Called during initial loading of the driver.
8482 */
8483static void
8484_scsih_probe_sas(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc)
8485{
8486 struct _sas_device *sas_device;
8487
8488 if (ioc->hide_drives)
8489 return;
8490
8491 while ((sas_device = get_next_sas_device(ioc))) {
8492 if (!mpt3sas_transport_port_add(ioc, sas_device->handle,
8493 sas_device->sas_address_parent)) {
8494 _scsih_sas_device_remove(ioc, sas_device);
8495 sas_device_put(sas_device);
8496 continue;
8497 } else if (!sas_device->starget) {
8498 /*
8499 * When asyn scanning is enabled, its not possible to
8500 * remove devices while scanning is turned on due to an
8501 * oops in scsi_sysfs_add_sdev()->add_device()->
8502 * sysfs_addrm_start()
8503 */
8504 if (!ioc->is_driver_loading) {
8505 mpt3sas_transport_port_remove(ioc,
8506 sas_device->sas_address,
8507 sas_device->sas_address_parent);
8508 _scsih_sas_device_remove(ioc, sas_device);
8509 sas_device_put(sas_device);
8510 continue;
8511 }
8512 }
8513 sas_device_make_active(ioc, sas_device);
8514 sas_device_put(sas_device);
8515 }
8516}
8517
8518/**
8519 * _scsih_probe_devices - probing for devices
8520 * @ioc: per adapter object
8521 *
8522 * Called during initial loading of the driver.
8523 */
8524static void
8525_scsih_probe_devices(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc)
8526{
8527 u16 volume_mapping_flags;
8528
8529 if (!(ioc->facts.ProtocolFlags & MPI2_IOCFACTS_PROTOCOL_SCSI_INITIATOR))
8530 return; /* return when IOC doesn't support initiator mode */
8531
8532 _scsih_probe_boot_devices(ioc);
8533
8534 if (ioc->ir_firmware) {
8535 volume_mapping_flags =
8536 le16_to_cpu(ioc->ioc_pg8.IRVolumeMappingFlags) &
8537 MPI2_IOCPAGE8_IRFLAGS_MASK_VOLUME_MAPPING_MODE;
8538 if (volume_mapping_flags ==
8539 MPI2_IOCPAGE8_IRFLAGS_LOW_VOLUME_MAPPING) {
8540 _scsih_probe_raid(ioc);
8541 _scsih_probe_sas(ioc);
8542 } else {
8543 _scsih_probe_sas(ioc);
8544 _scsih_probe_raid(ioc);
8545 }
8546 } else
8547 _scsih_probe_sas(ioc);
8548}
8549
8550/**
8551 * scsih_scan_start - scsi lld callback for .scan_start
8552 * @shost: SCSI host pointer
8553 *
8554 * The shost has the ability to discover targets on its own instead
8555 * of scanning the entire bus. In our implemention, we will kick off
8556 * firmware discovery.
8557 */
8558static void
8559scsih_scan_start(struct Scsi_Host *shost)
8560{
8561 struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc = shost_priv(shost);
8562 int rc;
8563 if (diag_buffer_enable != -1 && diag_buffer_enable != 0)
8564 mpt3sas_enable_diag_buffer(ioc, diag_buffer_enable);
8565
8566 if (disable_discovery > 0)
8567 return;
8568
8569 ioc->start_scan = 1;
8570 rc = mpt3sas_port_enable(ioc);
8571
8572 if (rc != 0)
8573 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "port enable: FAILED\n", ioc->name);
8574}
8575
8576/**
8577 * scsih_scan_finished - scsi lld callback for .scan_finished
8578 * @shost: SCSI host pointer
8579 * @time: elapsed time of the scan in jiffies
8580 *
8581 * This function will be called periodicallyn until it returns 1 with the
8582 * scsi_host and the elapsed time of the scan in jiffies. In our implemention,
8583 * we wait for firmware discovery to complete, then return 1.
8584 */
8585static int
8586scsih_scan_finished(struct Scsi_Host *shost, unsigned long time)
8587{
8588 struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc = shost_priv(shost);
8589
8590 if (disable_discovery > 0) {
8591 ioc->is_driver_loading = 0;
8592 ioc->wait_for_discovery_to_complete = 0;
8593 return 1;
8594 }
8595
8596 if (time >= (300 * HZ)) {
8597 ioc->base_cmds.status = MPT3_CMD_NOT_USED;
8598 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
8599 "port enable: FAILED with timeout (timeout=300s)\n",
8600 ioc->name);
8601 ioc->is_driver_loading = 0;
8602 return 1;
8603 }
8604
8605 if (ioc->start_scan)
8606 return 0;
8607
8608 if (ioc->start_scan_failed) {
8609 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
8610 "port enable: FAILED with (ioc_status=0x%08x)\n",
8611 ioc->name, ioc->start_scan_failed);
8612 ioc->is_driver_loading = 0;
8613 ioc->wait_for_discovery_to_complete = 0;
8614 ioc->remove_host = 1;
8615 return 1;
8616 }
8617
8618 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "port enable: SUCCESS\n", ioc->name);
8619 ioc->base_cmds.status = MPT3_CMD_NOT_USED;
8620
8621 if (ioc->wait_for_discovery_to_complete) {
8622 ioc->wait_for_discovery_to_complete = 0;
8623 _scsih_probe_devices(ioc);
8624 }
8625 mpt3sas_base_start_watchdog(ioc);
8626 ioc->is_driver_loading = 0;
8627 return 1;
8628}
