8667
8668/* shost template for SAS 3.0 HBA devices */
8669static struct scsi_host_template mpt3sas_driver_template = {
8670 .module = THIS_MODULE,
8671 .name = "Fusion MPT SAS Host",
8672 .proc_name = MPT3SAS_DRIVER_NAME,
8673 .queuecommand = scsih_qcmd,
8674 .target_alloc = scsih_target_alloc,
8675 .slave_alloc = scsih_slave_alloc,
8676 .slave_configure = scsih_slave_configure,
8677 .target_destroy = scsih_target_destroy,
8678 .slave_destroy = scsih_slave_destroy,
8679 .scan_finished = scsih_scan_finished,
8680 .scan_start = scsih_scan_start,
8681 .change_queue_depth = scsih_change_queue_depth,
8682 .eh_abort_handler = scsih_abort,
8683 .eh_device_reset_handler = scsih_dev_reset,
8684 .eh_target_reset_handler = scsih_target_reset,
8685 .eh_host_reset_handler = scsih_host_reset,
8686 .bios_param = scsih_bios_param,
8687 .can_queue = 1,
8688 .this_id = -1,
8689 .sg_tablesize = MPT3SAS_SG_DEPTH,
8690 .max_sectors = 32767,
8691 .cmd_per_lun = 7,
8692 .use_clustering = ENABLE_CLUSTERING,
8693 .shost_attrs = mpt3sas_host_attrs,
8694 .sdev_attrs = mpt3sas_dev_attrs,
8695 .track_queue_depth = 1,
8696};
8697
8698/* raid transport support for SAS 3.0 HBA devices */
8699static struct raid_function_template mpt3sas_raid_functions = {
8700 .cookie = &mpt3sas_driver_template,
8701 .is_raid = scsih_is_raid,
8702 .get_resync = scsih_get_resync,
8703 .get_state = scsih_get_state,
8704};
8705
8706/**
8707 * _scsih_determine_hba_mpi_version - determine in which MPI version class
8708 * this device belongs to.
8709 * @pdev: PCI device struct
8710 *
8711 * return MPI2_VERSION for SAS 2.0 HBA devices,
8712 * MPI25_VERSION for SAS 3.0 HBA devices, and
8713 * MPI26 VERSION for Cutlass & Invader SAS 3.0 HBA devices
8714 */
8715static u16
8716_scsih_determine_hba_mpi_version(struct pci_dev *pdev)
8717{
8718
8719 switch (pdev->device) {
8720 case MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SSS6200:
8721 case MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS2004:
8722 case MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS2008:
8723 case MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS2108_1:
8724 case MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS2108_2:
8725 case MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS2108_3:
8726 case MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS2116_1:
8727 case MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS2116_2:
8728 case MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS2208_1:
8729 case MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS2208_2:
8730 case MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS2208_3:
8731 case MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS2208_4:
8732 case MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS2208_5:
8733 case MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS2208_6:
8734 case MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS2308_1:
8735 case MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS2308_2:
8736 case MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS2308_3:
8737 return MPI2_VERSION;
8738 case MPI25_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3004:
8739 case MPI25_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3008:
8740 case MPI25_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3108_1:
8741 case MPI25_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3108_2:
8742 case MPI25_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3108_5:
8743 case MPI25_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3108_6:
8744 return MPI25_VERSION;
8745 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3216:
8746 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3224:
8747 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3316_1:
8748 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3316_2:
8749 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3316_3:
8750 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3316_4:
8751 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3324_1:
8752 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3324_2:
8753 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3324_3:
8754 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3324_4:
8755 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3508:
8756 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3508_1:
8757 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3408:
8758 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3516:
8759 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3516_1:
8760 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3416:
8761 return MPI26_VERSION;
8762 }
8763 return 0;
8764}
8765
8766/**
8767 * _scsih_probe - attach and add scsi host
8768 * @pdev: PCI device struct
8769 * @id: pci device id
8770 *
8771 * Returns 0 success, anything else error.
8772 */
8773static int
8774_scsih_probe(struct pci_dev *pdev, const struct pci_device_id *id)
8775{
8776 struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc;
8777 struct Scsi_Host *shost = NULL;
8778 int rv;
8779 u16 hba_mpi_version;
8780
8781 /* Determine in which MPI version class this pci device belongs */
8782 hba_mpi_version = _scsih_determine_hba_mpi_version(pdev);
8783 if (hba_mpi_version == 0)
8784 return -ENODEV;
8785
8786 /* Enumerate only SAS 2.0 HBA's if hbas_to_enumerate is one,
8787 * for other generation HBA's return with -ENODEV
8788 */
8789 if ((hbas_to_enumerate == 1) && (hba_mpi_version != MPI2_VERSION))
8790 return -ENODEV;
8791
8792 /* Enumerate only SAS 3.0 HBA's if hbas_to_enumerate is two,
8793 * for other generation HBA's return with -ENODEV
8794 */
8795 if ((hbas_to_enumerate == 2) && (!(hba_mpi_version == MPI25_VERSION
8796 || hba_mpi_version == MPI26_VERSION)))
8797 return -ENODEV;
8798
8799 switch (hba_mpi_version) {
8800 case MPI2_VERSION:
8801 pci_disable_link_state(pdev, PCIE_LINK_STATE_L0S |
8802 PCIE_LINK_STATE_L1 | PCIE_LINK_STATE_CLKPM);
8803 /* Use mpt2sas driver host template for SAS 2.0 HBA's */
8804 shost = scsi_host_alloc(&mpt2sas_driver_template,
8805 sizeof(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER));
8806 if (!shost)
8807 return -ENODEV;
8808 ioc = shost_priv(shost);
8809 memset(ioc, 0, sizeof(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER));
8810 ioc->hba_mpi_version_belonged = hba_mpi_version;
8811 ioc->id = mpt2_ids++;
8812 sprintf(ioc->driver_name, "%s", MPT2SAS_DRIVER_NAME);
8813 if (pdev->device == MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SSS6200) {
8814 ioc->is_warpdrive = 1;
8815 ioc->hide_ir_msg = 1;
8816 } else
8817 ioc->mfg_pg10_hide_flag = MFG_PAGE10_EXPOSE_ALL_DISKS;
8818 break;
8819 case MPI25_VERSION:
8820 case MPI26_VERSION:
8821 /* Use mpt3sas driver host template for SAS 3.0 HBA's */
8822 shost = scsi_host_alloc(&mpt3sas_driver_template,
8823 sizeof(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER));
8824 if (!shost)
8825 return -ENODEV;
8826 ioc = shost_priv(shost);
8827 memset(ioc, 0, sizeof(struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER));
8828 ioc->hba_mpi_version_belonged = hba_mpi_version;
8829 ioc->id = mpt3_ids++;
8830 sprintf(ioc->driver_name, "%s", MPT3SAS_DRIVER_NAME);
8831 switch (pdev->device) {
8832 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3508:
8833 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3508_1:
8834 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3408:
8835 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3516:
8836 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3516_1:
8837 case MPI26_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS3416:
8838 ioc->is_gen35_ioc = 1;
8839 break;
8840 default:
8841 ioc->is_gen35_ioc = 0;
8842 }
8843 if ((ioc->hba_mpi_version_belonged == MPI25_VERSION &&
8844 pdev->revision >= SAS3_PCI_DEVICE_C0_REVISION) ||
8845 (ioc->hba_mpi_version_belonged == MPI26_VERSION)) {
8846 ioc->combined_reply_queue = 1;
8847 if (ioc->is_gen35_ioc)
8848 ioc->combined_reply_index_count =
8849 MPT3_SUP_REPLY_POST_HOST_INDEX_REG_COUNT_G35;
8850 else
8851 ioc->combined_reply_index_count =
8852 MPT3_SUP_REPLY_POST_HOST_INDEX_REG_COUNT_G3;
8853 }
8854 break;
8855 default:
8856 return -ENODEV;
8857 }
8858
8859 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&ioc->list);
8860 spin_lock(&gioc_lock);
8861 list_add_tail(&ioc->list, &mpt3sas_ioc_list);
8862 spin_unlock(&gioc_lock);
8863 ioc->shost = shost;
8864 ioc->pdev = pdev;
8865 ioc->scsi_io_cb_idx = scsi_io_cb_idx;
8866 ioc->tm_cb_idx = tm_cb_idx;
8867 ioc->ctl_cb_idx = ctl_cb_idx;
8868 ioc->base_cb_idx = base_cb_idx;
8869 ioc->port_enable_cb_idx = port_enable_cb_idx;
8870 ioc->transport_cb_idx = transport_cb_idx;
8871 ioc->scsih_cb_idx = scsih_cb_idx;
8872 ioc->config_cb_idx = config_cb_idx;
8873 ioc->tm_tr_cb_idx = tm_tr_cb_idx;
8874 ioc->tm_tr_volume_cb_idx = tm_tr_volume_cb_idx;
8875 ioc->tm_sas_control_cb_idx = tm_sas_control_cb_idx;
8876 ioc->logging_level = logging_level;
8877 ioc->schedule_dead_ioc_flush_running_cmds = &_scsih_flush_running_cmds;
8878 /* misc semaphores and spin locks */
8879 mutex_init(&ioc->reset_in_progress_mutex);
8880 /* initializing pci_access_mutex lock */
8881 mutex_init(&ioc->pci_access_mutex);
8882 spin_lock_init(&ioc->ioc_reset_in_progress_lock);
8883 spin_lock_init(&ioc->scsi_lookup_lock);
8884 spin_lock_init(&ioc->sas_device_lock);
8885 spin_lock_init(&ioc->sas_node_lock);
8886 spin_lock_init(&ioc->fw_event_lock);
8887 spin_lock_init(&ioc->raid_device_lock);
8888 spin_lock_init(&ioc->diag_trigger_lock);
8889
8890 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&ioc->sas_device_list);
8891 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&ioc->sas_device_init_list);
8892 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&ioc->sas_expander_list);
8893 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&ioc->fw_event_list);
8894 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&ioc->raid_device_list);
8895 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&ioc->sas_hba.sas_port_list);
8896 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&ioc->delayed_tr_list);
8897 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&ioc->delayed_sc_list);
8898 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&ioc->delayed_event_ack_list);
8899 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&ioc->delayed_tr_volume_list);
8900 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&ioc->reply_queue_list);
8901
8902 sprintf(ioc->name, "%s_cm%d", ioc->driver_name, ioc->id);
8903
8904 /* init shost parameters */
8905 shost->max_cmd_len = 32;
8906 shost->max_lun = max_lun;
8907 shost->transportt = mpt3sas_transport_template;
8908 shost->unique_id = ioc->id;
8909
8910 if (max_sectors != 0xFFFF) {
8911 if (max_sectors < 64) {
8912 shost->max_sectors = 64;
8913 pr_warn(MPT3SAS_FMT "Invalid value %d passed " \
8914 "for max_sectors, range is 64 to 32767. Assigning "
8915 "value of 64.\n", ioc->name, max_sectors);
8916 } else if (max_sectors > 32767) {
8917 shost->max_sectors = 32767;
8918 pr_warn(MPT3SAS_FMT "Invalid value %d passed " \
8919 "for max_sectors, range is 64 to 32767. Assigning "
8920 "default value of 32767.\n", ioc->name,
8921 max_sectors);
8922 } else {
8923 shost->max_sectors = max_sectors & 0xFFFE;
8924 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
8925 "The max_sectors value is set to %d\n",
8926 ioc->name, shost->max_sectors);
8927 }
8928 }
8929
8930 /* register EEDP capabilities with SCSI layer */
8931 if (prot_mask > 0)
8932 scsi_host_set_prot(shost, prot_mask);
8933 else
8934 scsi_host_set_prot(shost, SHOST_DIF_TYPE1_PROTECTION
8935 | SHOST_DIF_TYPE2_PROTECTION
8936 | SHOST_DIF_TYPE3_PROTECTION);
8937
8938 scsi_host_set_guard(shost, SHOST_DIX_GUARD_CRC);
8939
8940 /* event thread */
8941 snprintf(ioc->firmware_event_name, sizeof(ioc->firmware_event_name),
8942 "fw_event_%s%d", ioc->driver_name, ioc->id);
8943 ioc->firmware_event_thread = alloc_ordered_workqueue(
8944 ioc->firmware_event_name, 0);
8945 if (!ioc->firmware_event_thread) {
8946 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
8947 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
8948 rv = -ENODEV;
8949 goto out_thread_fail;
8950 }
8951
8952 ioc->is_driver_loading = 1;
8953 if ((mpt3sas_base_attach(ioc))) {
8954 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
8955 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
8956 rv = -ENODEV;
8957 goto out_attach_fail;
8958 }
8959
8960 if (ioc->is_warpdrive) {
8961 if (ioc->mfg_pg10_hide_flag == MFG_PAGE10_EXPOSE_ALL_DISKS)
8962 ioc->hide_drives = 0;
8963 else if (ioc->mfg_pg10_hide_flag == MFG_PAGE10_HIDE_ALL_DISKS)
8964 ioc->hide_drives = 1;
8965 else {
8966 if (mpt3sas_get_num_volumes(ioc))
8967 ioc->hide_drives = 1;
8968 else
8969 ioc->hide_drives = 0;
8970 }
8971 } else
8972 ioc->hide_drives = 0;
8973
8974 rv = scsi_add_host(shost, &pdev->dev);
8975 if (rv) {
8976 pr_err(MPT3SAS_FMT "failure at %s:%d/%s()!\n",
8977 ioc->name, __FILE__, __LINE__, __func__);
8978 goto out_add_shost_fail;
8979 }
8980
8981 scsi_scan_host(shost);
8982 return 0;
8983out_add_shost_fail:
8984 mpt3sas_base_detach(ioc);
8985 out_attach_fail:
8986 destroy_workqueue(ioc->firmware_event_thread);
8987 out_thread_fail:
8988 spin_lock(&gioc_lock);
8989 list_del(&ioc->list);
8990 spin_unlock(&gioc_lock);
8991 scsi_host_put(shost);
8992 return rv;
8993}
8994
8995#ifdef CONFIG_PM
8996/**
8997 * scsih_suspend - power management suspend main entry point
8998 * @pdev: PCI device struct
8999 * @state: PM state change to (usually PCI_D3)
9000 *
9001 * Returns 0 success, anything else error.
9002 */
9003static int
9004scsih_suspend(struct pci_dev *pdev, pm_message_t state)
9005{
9006 struct Scsi_Host *shost = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
9007 struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc = shost_priv(shost);
9008 pci_power_t device_state;
9009
9010 mpt3sas_base_stop_watchdog(ioc);
9011 flush_scheduled_work();
9012 scsi_block_requests(shost);
9013 device_state = pci_choose_state(pdev, state);
9014 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
9015 "pdev=0x%p, slot=%s, entering operating state [D%d]\n",
9016 ioc->name, pdev, pci_name(pdev), device_state);
9017
9018 pci_save_state(pdev);
9019 mpt3sas_base_free_resources(ioc);
9020 pci_set_power_state(pdev, device_state);
9021 return 0;
9022}
9023
9024/**
9025 * scsih_resume - power management resume main entry point
9026 * @pdev: PCI device struct
9027 *
9028 * Returns 0 success, anything else error.
9029 */
9030static int
9031scsih_resume(struct pci_dev *pdev)
9032{
9033 struct Scsi_Host *shost = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
9034 struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc = shost_priv(shost);
9035 pci_power_t device_state = pdev->current_state;
9036 int r;
9037
9038 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT
9039 "pdev=0x%p, slot=%s, previous operating state [D%d]\n",
9040 ioc->name, pdev, pci_name(pdev), device_state);
9041
9042 pci_set_power_state(pdev, PCI_D0);
9043 pci_enable_wake(pdev, PCI_D0, 0);
9044 pci_restore_state(pdev);
9045 ioc->pdev = pdev;
9046 r = mpt3sas_base_map_resources(ioc);
9047 if (r)
9048 return r;
9049
9050 mpt3sas_base_hard_reset_handler(ioc, SOFT_RESET);
9051 scsi_unblock_requests(shost);
9052 mpt3sas_base_start_watchdog(ioc);
9053 return 0;
9054}
9055#endif /* CONFIG_PM */
9056
9057/**
9058 * scsih_pci_error_detected - Called when a PCI error is detected.
9059 * @pdev: PCI device struct
9060 * @state: PCI channel state
9061 *
9062 * Description: Called when a PCI error is detected.
9063 *
9064 * Return value:
9065 * PCI_ERS_RESULT_NEED_RESET or PCI_ERS_RESULT_DISCONNECT
9066 */
9067static pci_ers_result_t
9068scsih_pci_error_detected(struct pci_dev *pdev, pci_channel_state_t state)
9069{
9070 struct Scsi_Host *shost = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
9071 struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc = shost_priv(shost);
9072
9073 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "PCI error: detected callback, state(%d)!!\n",
9074 ioc->name, state);
9075
9076 switch (state) {
9077 case pci_channel_io_normal:
9078 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_CAN_RECOVER;
9079 case pci_channel_io_frozen:
9080 /* Fatal error, prepare for slot reset */
9081 ioc->pci_error_recovery = 1;
9082 scsi_block_requests(ioc->shost);
9083 mpt3sas_base_stop_watchdog(ioc);
9084 mpt3sas_base_free_resources(ioc);
9085 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_NEED_RESET;
9086 case pci_channel_io_perm_failure:
9087 /* Permanent error, prepare for device removal */
9088 ioc->pci_error_recovery = 1;
9089 mpt3sas_base_stop_watchdog(ioc);
9090 _scsih_flush_running_cmds(ioc);
9091 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_DISCONNECT;
9092 }
9093 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_NEED_RESET;
9094}
9095
9096/**
9097 * scsih_pci_slot_reset - Called when PCI slot has been reset.
9098 * @pdev: PCI device struct
9099 *
9100 * Description: This routine is called by the pci error recovery
9101 * code after the PCI slot has been reset, just before we
9102 * should resume normal operations.
9103 */
9104static pci_ers_result_t
9105scsih_pci_slot_reset(struct pci_dev *pdev)
9106{
9107 struct Scsi_Host *shost = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
9108 struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc = shost_priv(shost);
9109 int rc;
9110
9111 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "PCI error: slot reset callback!!\n",
9112 ioc->name);
9113
9114 ioc->pci_error_recovery = 0;
9115 ioc->pdev = pdev;
9116 pci_restore_state(pdev);
9117 rc = mpt3sas_base_map_resources(ioc);
9118 if (rc)
9119 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_DISCONNECT;
9120
9121 rc = mpt3sas_base_hard_reset_handler(ioc, FORCE_BIG_HAMMER);
9122
9123 pr_warn(MPT3SAS_FMT "hard reset: %s\n", ioc->name,
9124 (rc == 0) ? "success" : "failed");
9125
9126 if (!rc)
9127 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_RECOVERED;
9128 else
9129 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_DISCONNECT;
9130}
9131
9132/**
9133 * scsih_pci_resume() - resume normal ops after PCI reset
9134 * @pdev: pointer to PCI device
9135 *
9136 * Called when the error recovery driver tells us that its
9137 * OK to resume normal operation. Use completion to allow
9138 * halted scsi ops to resume.
9139 */
9140static void
9141scsih_pci_resume(struct pci_dev *pdev)
9142{
9143 struct Scsi_Host *shost = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
9144 struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc = shost_priv(shost);
9145
9146 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "PCI error: resume callback!!\n", ioc->name);
9147
9148 pci_cleanup_aer_uncorrect_error_status(pdev);
9149 mpt3sas_base_start_watchdog(ioc);
9150 scsi_unblock_requests(ioc->shost);
9151}
9152
9153/**
9154 * scsih_pci_mmio_enabled - Enable MMIO and dump debug registers
9155 * @pdev: pointer to PCI device
9156 */
9157static pci_ers_result_t
9158scsih_pci_mmio_enabled(struct pci_dev *pdev)
9159{
9160 struct Scsi_Host *shost = pci_get_drvdata(pdev);
9161 struct MPT3SAS_ADAPTER *ioc = shost_priv(shost);
9162
9163 pr_info(MPT3SAS_FMT "PCI error: mmio enabled callback!!\n",
9164 ioc->name);
9165
9166 /* TODO - dump whatever for debugging purposes */
9167
9168 /* This called only if scsih_pci_error_detected returns
9169 * PCI_ERS_RESULT_CAN_RECOVER. Read/write to the device still
9170 * works, no need to reset slot.
9171 */
9172 return PCI_ERS_RESULT_RECOVERED;
9173}
9174
9175/**
9176 * scsih__ncq_prio_supp - Check for NCQ command priority support
9177 * @sdev: scsi device struct
9178 *
9179 * This is called when a user indicates they would like to enable
9180 * ncq command priorities. This works only on SATA devices.
9181 */
9182bool scsih_ncq_prio_supp(struct scsi_device *sdev)
9183{
9184 unsigned char *buf;
9185 bool ncq_prio_supp = false;
9186
9187 if (!scsi_device_supports_vpd(sdev))
9188 return ncq_prio_supp;
9189
9190 buf = kmalloc(SCSI_VPD_PG_LEN, GFP_KERNEL);
9191 if (!buf)
9192 return ncq_prio_supp;
9193
9194 if (!scsi_get_vpd_page(sdev, 0x89, buf, SCSI_VPD_PG_LEN))
9195 ncq_prio_supp = (buf[213] >> 4) & 1;
9196
9197 kfree(buf);
9198 return ncq_prio_supp;
9199}
9200/*
9201 * The pci device ids are defined in mpi/mpi2_cnfg.h.
9202 */
9203static const struct pci_device_id mpt3sas_pci_table[] = {
9204 /* Spitfire ~ 2004 */
9205 { MPI2_MFGPAGE_VENDORID_LSI, MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS2004,
9206 PCI_ANY_ID, PCI_ANY_ID },
9207 /* Falcon ~ 2008 */
9208 { MPI2_MFGPAGE_VENDORID_LSI, MPI2_MFGPAGE_DEVID_SAS2008,

9298static struct pci_error_handlers _mpt3sas_err_handler = {
9299 .error_detected = scsih_pci_error_detected,
9300 .mmio_enabled = scsih_pci_mmio_enabled,
9301 .slot_reset = scsih_pci_slot_reset,
9302 .resume = scsih_pci_resume,
9303};
9304
9305static struct pci_driver mpt3sas_driver = {
9306 .name = MPT3SAS_DRIVER_NAME,
9307 .id_table = mpt3sas_pci_table,
9308 .probe = _scsih_probe,
9309 .remove = scsih_remove,
9310 .shutdown = scsih_shutdown,
9311 .err_handler = &_mpt3sas_err_handler,
9312#ifdef CONFIG_PM
9313 .suspend = scsih_suspend,
9314 .resume = scsih_resume,
9315#endif
9316};
9317
9318/**
9319 * scsih_init - main entry point for this driver.
9320 *
9321 * Returns 0 success, anything else error.
9322 */
9323static int
9324scsih_init(void)
9325{
9326 mpt2_ids = 0;
9327 mpt3_ids = 0;
9328
9329 mpt3sas_base_initialize_callback_handler();
9330
9331 /* queuecommand callback hander */
9332 scsi_io_cb_idx = mpt3sas_base_register_callback_handler(_scsih_io_done);
9333
9334 /* task management callback handler */
9335 tm_cb_idx = mpt3sas_base_register_callback_handler(_scsih_tm_done);
9336
9337 /* base internal commands callback handler */
9338 base_cb_idx = mpt3sas_base_register_callback_handler(mpt3sas_base_done);
9339 port_enable_cb_idx = mpt3sas_base_register_callback_handler(
9340 mpt3sas_port_enable_done);
9341
9342 /* transport internal commands callback handler */
9343 transport_cb_idx = mpt3sas_base_register_callback_handler(
9344 mpt3sas_transport_done);
9345
9346 /* scsih internal commands callback handler */
9347 scsih_cb_idx = mpt3sas_base_register_callback_handler(_scsih_done);
9348
9349 /* configuration page API internal commands callback handler */
9350 config_cb_idx = mpt3sas_base_register_callback_handler(
9351 mpt3sas_config_done);
9352
9353 /* ctl module callback handler */
9354 ctl_cb_idx = mpt3sas_base_register_callback_handler(mpt3sas_ctl_done);
9355
9356 tm_tr_cb_idx = mpt3sas_base_register_callback_handler(
9357 _scsih_tm_tr_complete);
9358
9359 tm_tr_volume_cb_idx = mpt3sas_base_register_callback_handler(
9360 _scsih_tm_volume_tr_complete);
9361
9362 tm_sas_control_cb_idx = mpt3sas_base_register_callback_handler(
9363 _scsih_sas_control_complete);
9364
9365 return 0;
9366}
9367
9368/**
9369 * scsih_exit - exit point for this driver (when it is a module).
9370 *
9371 * Returns 0 success, anything else error.
9372 */
9373static void
9374scsih_exit(void)
9375{
9376
9377 mpt3sas_base_release_callback_handler(scsi_io_cb_idx);
9378 mpt3sas_base_release_callback_handler(tm_cb_idx);
9379 mpt3sas_base_release_callback_handler(base_cb_idx);
9380 mpt3sas_base_release_callback_handler(port_enable_cb_idx);
9381 mpt3sas_base_release_callback_handler(transport_cb_idx);
9382 mpt3sas_base_release_callback_handler(scsih_cb_idx);
9383 mpt3sas_base_release_callback_handler(config_cb_idx);
9384 mpt3sas_base_release_callback_handler(ctl_cb_idx);
9385
9386 mpt3sas_base_release_callback_handler(tm_tr_cb_idx);
9387 mpt3sas_base_release_callback_handler(tm_tr_volume_cb_idx);
9388 mpt3sas_base_release_callback_handler(tm_sas_control_cb_idx);
9389
9390/* raid transport support */
9391 if (hbas_to_enumerate != 1)
9392 raid_class_release(mpt3sas_raid_template);
9393 if (hbas_to_enumerate != 2)
9394 raid_class_release(mpt2sas_raid_template);
9395 sas_release_transport(mpt3sas_transport_template);
9396}
9397
9398/**
9399 * _mpt3sas_init - main entry point for this driver.
9400 *
9401 * Returns 0 success, anything else error.
9402 */
9403static int __init
9404_mpt3sas_init(void)
9405{
9406 int error;
9407
9408 pr_info("%s version %s loaded\n", MPT3SAS_DRIVER_NAME,
9409 MPT3SAS_DRIVER_VERSION);
9410
9411 mpt3sas_transport_template =
9412 sas_attach_transport(&mpt3sas_transport_functions);
9413 if (!mpt3sas_transport_template)
9414 return -ENODEV;
9415
9416 /* No need attach mpt3sas raid functions template
9417 * if hbas_to_enumarate value is one.
9418 */
9419 if (hbas_to_enumerate != 1) {
9420 mpt3sas_raid_template =
9421 raid_class_attach(&mpt3sas_raid_functions);
9422 if (!mpt3sas_raid_template) {
9423 sas_release_transport(mpt3sas_transport_template);
9424 return -ENODEV;
9425 }
9426 }
9427
9428 /* No need to attach mpt2sas raid functions template
9429 * if hbas_to_enumarate value is two
9430 */
9431 if (hbas_to_enumerate != 2) {
9432 mpt2sas_raid_template =
9433 raid_class_attach(&mpt2sas_raid_functions);
9434 if (!mpt2sas_raid_template) {
9435 sas_release_transport(mpt3sas_transport_template);
9436 return -ENODEV;
9437 }
9438 }
9439
9440 error = scsih_init();
9441 if (error) {
9442 scsih_exit();
9443 return error;
9444 }
9445
9446 mpt3sas_ctl_init(hbas_to_enumerate);
9447
9448 error = pci_register_driver(&mpt3sas_driver);
9449 if (error)
9450 scsih_exit();
9451
9452 return error;
9453}
9454
9455/**
9456 * _mpt3sas_exit - exit point for this driver (when it is a module).
9457 *
9458 */
9459static void __exit
9460_mpt3sas_exit(void)
9461{
9462 pr_info("mpt3sas version %s unloading\n",
9463 MPT3SAS_DRIVER_VERSION);
9464
9465 pci_unregister_driver(&mpt3sas_driver);
9466
9467 mpt3sas_ctl_exit(hbas_to_enumerate);
9468
9469 scsih_exit();
9470}
9471
9472module_init(_mpt3sas_init);
9473module_exit(_mpt3sas_exit);
